{"name":"Spontaneous Casting Tools","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character must use casting tools to cast spontaneous spells just as he does for casting formulaic spells. He has 15 individual tools, one for each Art, which he must use in various combinations to cast spontaneous spells. This Flaw can only be taken by Verditius magi.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"spontaneous-casting-tools","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922704726,"modifiedTime":1730929086778,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"00g2C9YS1sQdeTMf","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Missing Hand","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Perhaps it was an accident or a punishment in your past that cost you one of your hands. Climbing, combat, and other activities normally requiring both hands are at a penalty of –3 or greater.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"missing-hand","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"06U43sDyOzTq6P25","sort":2600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Dark Secret","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are haunted by something that would lead to shame, rejection, and possibly revenge if discovered. Hints about the secret continually arise, and there might be others who know it and could betray you. This makes you avoid certain places, dislike certain people, or fear certain things.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"dark-secret","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730785255734,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"08K2bHLN7Ha2nmMb","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Manifest Sin","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A sin or crime this character has committed in the past stains his spirit and is manifest to those who can perceive things hidden to mortal senses. Characters with Second Sight, Sense Holiness &amp; Unholiness, or similar Supernatural Powers or Abilities perceive the sin through one or more senses.&nbsp;</p><p>The manifestation of the sin or crime should be chosen by you and the storyguide together, and should always be appropriate to the sin or crime in question. For instance, the perpetrator of a violent crime may appear to have blood on his hands, or be accompanied by the sobbing of his victim, while lustful sins may be seen to play across the sinner’s leering face.&nbsp;</p><p>In addition, the character suffer a –1 penalty to all social interaction rolls or totals as the intangible aura of their past sins affects those with whom they interact.&nbsp;</p><p>While his spirit is tainted and the manifestation will always be with him, he may spend a Faith Point, including Faith Points gained from taking Holy Communion and from relics, to banish the manifestation for Sun duration. While banished, the sin cannot be perceived and the social penalty is also suspended.&nbsp;</p><p>This Flaw originates from either the Divine or the Infernal Realm, as a mark of punishment, penitence, or temptation.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"manifest-sin","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730465364878,"modifiedTime":1730929086798,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0JJUSD1QUmtqnlim","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Curse of Slander","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Wherever he stays, unpleasant rumors and ill-favored stories about this character begin to spread within a short time. This can be due to bad luck, or it could be something supernatural, like a curse. The slander is centered on one specific section of mundane society — the nobility, the church, guilds, peasants — and it seriously hampers his working life. After staying one season in an area, he gains a bad Reputation at level 1, usually a Local Reputation. He gains one point toward raising the Reputation in each further season, or more if he is involved in disturbing or strange events. Truly remarkable deeds can halt the increase for one season, but they will be forgotten come next season. At a covenant, people are used to strange things and deviant behavior. The Reputation is gained and increases in intervals of years rather than seasons, giving the poor victim more time before he becomes completely shunned. If the character leaves an area, the Reputation stops increasing, and may even fall, at the troupe’s discretion.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"curse-of-slander","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729924045096,"modifiedTime":1730929086823,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0OCR5zMp6hEyxLoj","sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Chaotic Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Your magic is very wild. When you cast a spontaneous spell, you must specify a desired level of effect. If you fall short of or exceed that target by more than one level, the spell still works, but its effects are beyond your control—the storyguide decides the results. The level of effect includes any levels you assign to Penetration.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"chaotic-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730757360591,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"0Yh56spJVh3LLg8f","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Vendetta","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The magus is engaged in one of House Verditius’ vendettas, mostly likely carrying on his parens’s vendetta against another Verditius magus. This vendetta stops just short of physical injury to him or the other. Neither of them will bring this feud to the Quaesitores, wishing to finish it themselves. The magus with whom he is feuding must be an NPC, who regularly takes some sort of action with which the character must contend. This Flaw is generally restricted to magi of House Verditius, as the custom of vendetta is limited to that House. Other characters should take Enemy or Feud to represent a similar situation.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"vendetta","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926866595,"modifiedTime":1730929086838,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0cdNKKlbAoNPTE3c","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Reckless - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You tend not to notice that situations are threatening, and certainly do not stop to consider whether they might be. You just go ahead and charge right in.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"reckless","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925459523,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"1BZRikH0Xgvigr3X","sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Sleep Disorder","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">More often than not, this character is unable to sleep soundly during the night. The resulting deprivation means that he is likely to nod off in periods of quiet and boredom. When the character is alone, comfortable, bored, or otherwise at risk of falling asleep, he needs to make a suitable Personality roll to avoid nodding off. Loyal, Reliable, and Lazy (for a penalty in the last case) are all appropriate. The character’s current Fatigue penalty applies to the roll.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Regardless of whether he manages to stay awake, the following night you must make a stress roll (no botch) against an Ease Factor of 6 to see if the character sleeps well. Every night he has slept poorly, he loses a Long Term Fatigue Level. Continue this until he sleeps soundly for a whole night. Once he has lost 3 Long Term Fatigue Levels, he automatically sleeps through the night, due to sheer exhaustion. This Flaw is not compatible with the Night Ter- rors Flaw.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"sleep-disorder","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922370977,"modifiedTime":1730929086851,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"1FaQrv4quMiPtYc3","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Compulsion - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have an unfortunate urge that you have trouble resisting. Examples include drinking, sex, perfection, bragging, or gambling.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"compulsion-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"1GFt2qlp03OhJp55","sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Independent Craftsman","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This character has his own way of working and doesn’t like other people getting in his way. This character always treats his Leadership and Craft or Profession Abilities as three levels lower when working with others on a given task. For Craftsmen, this means that whether he is working as an assistant or working with assistants his Craft Ability has a penalty of –3. This affects the number of assistants he can employ in the workshop and the benefit that he provides when working as an assistant. If you are not using the rules in <em>City and Guild</em> (page 73), treat this is a Personality Flaw.&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"independent-craftsman","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730457890255,"modifiedTime":1730929086865,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"1In7d0YrEKlCtvHI","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Manufactured Ignorance","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The tainted person has a delusion, but his mistaken belief is sustained by a group of minor demons that provide a stream of supporting evidence. Different groups of demons create varying delusions for tainted people. Many such people believe they have a glorious destiny, and the world smiles at their efforts, because the demons make it appear so. Hermetic demon hunters have found more than one child who believed he was the final scion of a noble house.&nbsp;</p><p>In each story, the character receives one minor, fortunate occurrence that confirms his rosy view of life. Minor fortunate occurrences are situations demons can arrange surreptitiously ahead of time. They may include a character arriving at an inn where the last room is available, finding an important door unlocked, or a coal from the fireplace mysteriously extinguishing itself on the floor rushes.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"manufactured-ignorance","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730465397494,"modifiedTime":1730929086881,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"1OyYPDIzR5g88dbH","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Repellent","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character has developed one of the physical characteristics of his demonic creator, which causes fear and revulsion among normal humans. The character makes all rolls requiring trust with a –6 penalty. The character also gains a minor advantage from the repellent feature. As examples, a character with horns, claws, or fangs could learn to use them in melee, a scaled character might have a Soak bonus of +3, and a character with demonic eyes might see in the dark.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"repellent","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true},"effects":[],"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730921705759,"modifiedTime":1730929086899,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"1R47fClcE4opLT0f","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Afflicted Tongue","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[{"_id":"qZY93ZsEnKaJvz1C","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"origin":"Compendium.arm5e.flaws.hADonI8WjhRHoERP","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":[],"subtype":[],"option":[]}},"name":"Speach impediment","description":"","statuses":[],"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null},"img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","type":"base","system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have a speech impediment, such as a lisp, stutter, or missing teeth. You suffer a –2 penalty to all rolls involving the voice, and all Casting Scores if you cast the spell using words. If you are a magus, you must also roll an extra botch die when casting a spell using words.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"afflicted-tongue","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"1SEkDzEOdFaZKaJE","sort":2800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Failed Monk","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You were once a member of a cloistered order, but were cast out for some great sin or gross incompetence, or perhaps you ran away and your abbot might allow you to come back after a suitable punishment. Because of this, you have a poor Reputation at level 2 in the local area and within the Church. You no longer need to observe your monastic vows of poverty, chastity, and obedience, though you may still practice them as they might be ingrained in your nature. You may take Academic Abilities during character creation.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Female characters may take this Flaw as Failed Nun.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"failed-monk","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"socialWestern","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"49M5jwoqSphEsyDt","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013651911,"modifiedTime":1730929086918,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"1TpDQx7w6jdq4aLu","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Baneful Circumstances","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Something about the character’s supernatural nature weakens him in relatively common circumstances, such as when touching the ground or when in the presence of women. At these times, the character cannot recover Fatigue, heal wounds, or recover Might, and if at the end of the year the character has spent more than half of his time subject to these conditions, he must make an additional Aging roll even if he is normally immune to aging because of a Longevity Ritual or Might Score.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"baneful-circumstances","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729917979297,"modifiedTime":1730929086933,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"1jslnTkC8yoX3mDL","sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Twilight Prone","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You either enjoy or cannot help running excessive amounts of magic through you when you cast spells. You must roll to resist Twilight on a single magical botch, rather than on a double botch like most magi.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"twilight-prone","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730926132690,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"1tRWI5HaSr2vK5lI","sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Primitive Equipment","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character is capable of using only the simplest tools and equipment. Perhaps her training was incomplete, or she has been affected by some sort of curse, or maybe she originates from a less technologically-capable society and refuses to adapt. She is restricted to Inexpensive weapons and armor only, regardless of what is made available to her. If forced by order or necessity to use other equipment, her Burden is one point higher when she uses anything other than Inexpensive weapons, and one point higher when she uses anything other than Inexpensive armor. She suffers a –1 penalty to Attack and Defense if using inappropriate weapons, and a –1 penalty to Initiative and Protection if using inappropriate armor. If the character works as a laborer or craftsman, she uses simple tools and primitive procedures. Unless working with simple tasks, the base Craft Value (see <em>City & Guild</em>, page 67) is raised by 1–3 at the storyguide’s discretion, based on complexity. Further, her workshop may not be improved with regards to Innovation (<em>City & Guild</em>, page 65). Other Profession Abilities dependent on tools and equipment suffer a similar penalty for complex tasks. You should only take this Flaw if the character belongs to a profession that relies heavily on equipment, such as a smith, mason, or soldier.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"primitive-equipment","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730919429210,"modifiedTime":1730929086948,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"1tx2QnkzFbn2EF3c","sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Hatred (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You hate someone or some group so much that hurting them dominates your life. The target of your hatred must not be someone you could easily overcome.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"hatred-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730529742704,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"2ARX4qIP6rQN32qI","sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Pagan - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You do not follow the teachings of the Church, and have never been baptized. This tends to upset those in authority in Mythic Europe and frighten common people who learn of it. You do not observe Christian holidays, and you try to avoid churchmen and the Dominion. You cannot pretend to go along with society, however, because you believe that it would displease your gods and incur their wrath — you might suffer grave supernatural consequences if you take Communion or appear to worship gods other than your own. You may begin with Magic Lore or Faerie Lore, depending on the specifics of your faith. (This is not a Flaw in areas of Mythic Europe with substantial pagan populations, but by 1220 the only such areas are in parts of the Novgorod Tribunal. It may also be a Minor Flaw for grogs who live at a covenant with a substantial pagan population that is an accepted and open part of the covenant community.)</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"pagan-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730529483933,"modifiedTime":1730929086960,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"2g2R3BTmPNJELBZB","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Wrathful (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are prone to anger over the smallest issues, and your rage when you are thwarted in something major is terrible to behold.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"wrathful-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928974175,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"2zUHgr3ex1oehsFo","sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Obese","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[{"_id":"RV7UuhWSSU7fHDn1","changes":[{"key":"system.vitals.siz.value","value":"1","mode":2,"priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"origin":"Compendium.arm5e.flaws.simXyBekUThIdt2Q","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["vitals"],"subtype":["size"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Size +1","description":"","statuses":[],"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null},"img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","type":"base","system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are large because of fat, not muscle. You are at –1 to all rolls that involve moving quickly or gracefully and at –3 to all Fatigue rolls. You are not so large that your Size is increased, and you may take this Flaw along with the Virtues and Flaws that change your Size.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"obese","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"3NUTVZLNMeA4yZxY","sort":2900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Exciting Experimentation","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Your character’s experiments tend to have a flair for the ... dramatic. When rolling on any of the experimentation tables, roll two dice instead of the normal one. The storyguide then chooses and applies the more amusing of your two results.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"exciting-experimentation","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013376227,"modifiedTime":1730929086974,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"3TMoGezHbyiIuvAq","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Slow Power","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">One of the character’s supernatural powers is very slow, so that it requires an additional round of preparation to activate. This Flaw may be taken more than once, if the character has multiple powers, but not more than once for a single power.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"slow-power","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922480465,"modifiedTime":1730929086987,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"3pNzl0peiDpNR8gS","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"False Power","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">One of the character’s Supernatural Virtues is associated with the Infernal realm, in addition to the realm with which it would normally be associated, which causes it to appear unholy when subjected to Divine or Infernal. This quality could be because of something inherent to the Power, or perhaps because of the interference of Infernal agents.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">This Flaw can apply to Supernatural Virtues that define the character’s background, like Faerie Blood, Diedne Magic, or even The Gift. In these cases, falsehood permeates the whole of the character’s being, causing everything she does to seem unholy to those with the ability to sense it.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">The False Power is often subtly changed by its Infernal aspect, making it more sinister or negative. Here are some examples:</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\"><strong>(False) Premonitions:</strong> The taint of the character’s Premonitions Power leaves it vulnerable to Infernal manipulation, even if the character has Magic Resistance. Many of the character’s premonitions are accurate, and pursuit of the stories they evoke is usually worthwhile. These valuable insights often lead characters to trust lies that a demon offers through the Power in order to manipulate their response to pivotal events.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\"><strong>(False) Second Sight:</strong> The character is particularly likely to see through an illusion or deception when what he sees would lead him to sin. Sometimes he may see through mundane obstacles, if the information gained would tempt him to sinful acts.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\"><strong>(False) Shapeshifter:</strong> The character can change his shape, but only into animals typically associated with the Infernal, such as a cat, a wolf, a raven, or a rat. When in these shapes, he seems unholy to those can recognize that quality.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">It is quite possible that the character does not know that his Power is false. Once he does, he may find himself in a moral dilemma. Most people consider it a sin to use Powers associated with the Infernal realm for any reason, and would label him an infernalist if they discovered the nature of his Power. Yet his Power is also associated with another realm, making it more difficult to recognize it as Infernal, and leaving it unclear whether the Power is inherently evil or simply tainted by association. Perhaps the character believes it is not wrong for him to use his Powers, so long as he does not pursue evil ends with them.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">Once the character recognizes that the Power has an unholy aspect, he may choose to treat it as an Infernal Power at any time, using the Infernal Power column of the realm interaction chart and thus giving him a bonus in Infernal auras. This may also grant him other benefits: like other infernalists he can boost his casting total with sacrifices, and use an Infernal Ceremony to include others in the activation, as described in <em>Realms of Power: The Infernal,</em> page 91. However, doing this removes any illusions about the Power’s realm — even magical and faerie Powers can recognize that it is Infernal.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">If the character realizes his Power is corrupted, he may decide to seek help from the Divine. Sincere repentance and participation in a form of ceremonial absolution allow the character to lose this Flaw, though this also takes away the Virtue it modifies. This is a heavy penance, but it is the only way to exorcise the evil influence of the Infernal realm, and of course there are far greater rewards in Heaven.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">This Flaw may be taken multiple times, once for each appropriate Supernatural Virtue that the character possesses, but in each subsequent instance as a Minor Flaw rather than a Major one. Also note that this Flaw cannot apply to Supernatural Virtues that are affiliated to the Infernal realm in the first place, and the troupe may not allow it to apply to Virtues derived from the Divine.</span></p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"false-power","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013866535,"modifiedTime":1730929086999,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"3v8979v9u8ndXzCt","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Loose Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Your Advancement Total is halved whenever you try to Master spells.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"loose-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756699693,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"40ZzrOTxkRTzYq9j","sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Poor Hearing","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Subtract 3 from rolls involving hearing. Speech that is hard for others to understand because of language, dialect, or accent is almost impossible for you to follow. You often pretend to be listening to people when in fact you are not.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"poor-hearing","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925470182,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"4XOLrwmTOdRWBOEc","sort":3000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Waster Of Vis","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">When you use raw vis you waste one quarter (rounded up) of the pawns you apply. The lost raw vis does not apply to the magical effect being enacted but does count toward the total number of botch dice you must roll if you roll a zero. You must use a third again as many pawns as usual when casting a ritual spell, and if you want to improve an Art score by studying raw vis, you must use a third again as many pawns as usual. This Flaw applies to all occasions on which you use vis, including certamen, laboratory work, and boosting penetration. Wasted pawns count toward the maximum number you can use at one time.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">For example, if you would normally use 12 pawns, you must use 16, and 4, one quarter of those you use, are wasted. If you would normally need 10 pawns, you must use 14, because 4 pawns are wasted.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"waster-of-vis","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928562895,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"4aOpu5R2t0mtKcj3","sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Low Tolerance","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character cannot easily withstand pain and fatigue. Increase the penalties for reduced Fatigue levels by one point, and increase the total penalty from wounds the character has received by one point. You also suffer a –3 penalty on rolls for the character to resist pain.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"low-tolerance","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730465105242,"modifiedTime":1730929087013,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"4kZEBJvbh92xARs7","sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Unspecialized","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character does not have any specialties for any of her Abilities.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"unspecialized","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926748138,"modifiedTime":1730929087026,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"4uVbcfRyWl2PbK3t","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Magical Fascination","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>This character is intensely interested in supernatural and magical phenomena, to the exclusion of all other motivations. It is as if his life is hollow and drab without these experiences. He will involve himself in any supernatural investigation, social encounter, or confrontation. He must try and find out as much as he can about it, and he is curious and has busy hands, definitely trying to take souvenirs. To represent the scraps of knowledge he has, he is allowed to have a score of 1 (but no more) in either Magic or Faerie Lore at character creation. But most of the time, he is filling in the blanks himself and making it up as he goes along, enthusiastically.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"magical-fascination","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730465315937,"modifiedTime":1730929087039,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"502PcH4xfNGVRL4T","sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Driven (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have some goal which you are determined to bring about. This has to be the sort of big goal that could shape an entire life, but if you do accomplish it you will immediately turn to a new project.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"driven-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730784507654,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"5HQ8rFGGJLD0U3cw","sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Magic Addiction","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You crave the rush of casting and holding power over magic. Whenever you cast a spell, you have a difficult time stopping yourself from casting again and again until you drop from exhaustion. Whenever you use a stress die in spellcasting, you must, whether or not the spell succeeds, make an Intelligence + Concentration stress roll, against an Ease Factor of half the level of the spell (or, if you botched, the level you were attempting). If you fail, as your next action you must either cast a Formulaic spell of at least the same level as the previous spell, or cast any spontaneous spell, expending Fatigue and not reserving levels for Penetration. You must roll again to control your addiction, based on the level of the spell you just cast, but you get a +3 bonus to the roll for every spell you cast after the first. If you botch, you continue casting spells until you fall unconscious.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"magic-addiction","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756699776,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"5RtSeEHhjMB9GzPF","sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Bound Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">When you die, all of your spells end abruptly and any magic items that you created cease to function. You cannot take this Flaw with Harnessed Magic (page @@), as that Virtue already includes this effect.</span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"bound-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918425438,"modifiedTime":1730929087055,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"5XPUzcE3VKDDOqvJ","sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weak Parens","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your parens was less powerful or a worse teacher than normal. You gain 60 fewer experience points and 30 fewer spell levels from apprenticeship, for a total of 180 experience points and 90 levels of spells.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"weak-parens","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928696759,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"5irihYp5vooRJpku","sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Fury","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A violent temper sometimes overwhelms you, sending you into a destructive, uncontrollable rage. You are likely to be provoked by some sort of specific event, such as being insulted, being hurt, or hearing the Order of Hermes disparaged. Roll 9+ on a stress die to avoid flying into a rage when such an event occurs, with another roll every round to try to calm yourself should you fail the first. On a botch, you try to kill everyone around you. While enraged you get +3 to Damage, but –1 on all other scores and rolls.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"fury","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730785367430,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"5j8nkvlhg4y4CCSj","sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Lost Love","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have lost your true love to death, distance, or marriage. You take little joy in life’s pleasures and give up easily in the face of difficulty, since you’ve already lost the most important struggle. On those occasions when you forget yourself and have a good time, you inevitably feel sorrow afterwards, thinking about how it could have been if your love were with you.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"lost-love","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"5oDRHgsHyOs30H8A","sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Compulsive Lying - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Telling the truth is really hard for this character. This does not apply in situations where the answer is evident and any lie would be transparent; he does not claim that the sky is green under normal conditions. However, when he cannot be immediately caught out, he finds it hard to avoid embellishing stories, or simply making them up. Perhaps he wants to make himself look good, perhaps he wants to downplay his own part in a conflict, or perhaps he just loves the power of confusing people.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"compulsion-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729923298518,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"5twwwGxPe4RMqa0l","sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Offensive to (Beings)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This Flaw is associated with one of six classes of beings: animals, mundane humans, divine beings, faeries, demons, or magical creatures. These last four include characters associated with the Divine, Faerie, Infernal, or Magic realm, respectively, through Supernatural Virtues or Flaws, as well as beings with Might.&nbsp;</p><p>Beings of the chosen category react badly to the character, as if he had The Gift, which makes them very uncomfortable around him and gives him a –3 to all social interaction rolls with them.&nbsp;</p><p>You may not take this Flaw more than once; characters who are Offensive to more than one kind of being should take Magical Air instead. Characters with The Gift may take this Flaw only if they have the Gentle Gift, which makes this type of being react to them negatively while others are unaffected. Characters with Magical Air may not take it at all.</p><p>If you are offensive to animals, animals with a Might score react in different ways. In general, those that react negatively to The Gift react negatively to you, while those that react positively do not, unless you actually have The Gift.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"offensive-to-beings","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730528955347,"modifiedTime":1730929087068,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"5ycRqrTmNFbHSx7h","sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Employed by Company","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Characters with this Flaw are salaried employees, answerable to an employer, which is normally a merchant company. They may be merchants who travel on behalf of a company, or administrators who are answerable to the partners. On the other hand, they are also backed up by the resources of the company. This Flaw may also be used for salaried employees of other organizations.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"employed-by-company","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730012910702,"modifiedTime":1730929087083,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"608dxDNV80D5YLxR","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Outlaw","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_da50amwz3qe","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have been outlawed, and must live by your wits outside society. You may take Martial Abilities at character generation, and have a Reputation at level 2 for whatever got you outlawed. Outlaw followers created as grogs should take the Branded Criminal, Outcast or Wanderer social status.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"outlaw","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756699901,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"VkWchgUydFoqpyYF","_id":"61Y61dP75VwqubIK","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Missing Eye","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You cannot judge close distances easily and get –3 on Attack rolls for missiles and targeting rolls for spells. In melee combat you suffer –1 on Attack rolls because your field of vision is limited. You also have a blind side from which people can approach unseen. This Flaw can be combined with Poor Eyesight, but the penalties are cumulative.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"missing-eye","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"63KQAPU15PvB1ZeD","sort":3100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Vulnerable Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character’s magic is automatically dispelled in certain uncommon circumstances. Examples include: when touching iron, when under the influence of the Divine, when crossing over running water, when his name is spoken three times, or when he is not touching the ground. This condition immediately ends the duration of a spell when it is applied to the target, or all of your active spells when applied to you.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This Flaw may be taken multiple times, so long as a different condition is specified for each. It may not be combined with Restrictions or Necessary Conditions that have the same (or equivalent) conditions.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"vulnerable-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730927190955,"modifiedTime":1730929087097,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"69PbauDqvDA35ql7","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Dependent","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You feel responsible for someone, and bound to help if they are in trouble. This person may be a relative or friend, but should be relatively weak and a non-player character. If your Dependent passes beyond your ability to help, or becomes too powerful, you should substitute another Story Flaw. Possibilities include taking the children of the old Dependent as new dependents, taking the killers of the Dependent as Enemies, or taking the Dependent as a True Friend.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"dependent","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730785270171,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"6F3oirP5GvH083zw","sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Pagan - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You do not follow the teachings of the Church, and have never been baptized. This tends to upset those in authority in Mythic Europe and frighten common people who learn of it. You do not observe Christian holidays, and you try to avoid churchmen and the Dominion. You cannot pretend to go along with society, however, because you believe that it would displease your gods and incur their wrath — you might suffer grave supernatural consequences if you take Communion or appear to worship gods other than your own. You may begin with Magic Lore or Faerie Lore, depending on the specifics of your faith. (This is not a Flaw in areas of Mythic Europe with substantial pagan populations, but by 1220 the only such areas are in parts of the Novgorod Tribunal. It may also be a Minor Flaw for grogs who live at a covenant with a substantial pagan population that is an accepted and open part of the covenant community.)</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"pagan-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730529463061,"modifiedTime":1730929087113,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"6bVuNJKUjV1044x5","sort":6000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Favors","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You owe a boon to someone (or to a great many people), and may be called upon to return the favor at any time. The consequences of ignoring such a request can range from mild to deadly serious, at the storyguide’s discretion.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"favors","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013908946,"modifiedTime":1730929087131,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"6c7eFHlupqDvJnlQ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Tragic Life","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character’s life has been manipulated by demons to ensure that she will act in a certain way in response to important events, usually to her own detriment and in such a way as to further a particular demon’s aims. This means that she is a tainted character.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Tainted characters are produced as tools, to influence pivotal events. This Flaw represents two factors: the events that the demons have designed the person to influence are likely to happen, and the person has been designed and conditioned to behave predictably when her moment of destiny arrives. Tainted people are likely, at their point of destiny, to choose to sin, and so cause terrible events. The repercussions of the tragedy they create often harm the tainted person. The predisposition toward sin at the character’s pivotal moment should be represented with a sinful Personality Trait.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Tainted people have difficult lives, but are not doomed from the moment of their conception. They have five sources of hope.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Demons do not foresee the future, they simply predict it through extremely skilled judgments. Arbitrary occurrences can ruin their schemes.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The process of creating and training tainted people contains random factors. These include inherited Flaws, like Tainted with Evil or Disfigured, which are personally painful, but might distance the character from her designed destiny.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character’s relationships with other humans also provide unpredictable elements. Most significantly, virtuous humans may notice the tainted person’s tendency toward a certain type of sin, and teach them to resist it.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Humans have free will. All deception aside, the tainted person still has the power to choose not to perform sins. The tainted person may not understand this, or may feel that the sin she performed is minor and justified given the situation in which she is presented with her choice, but the choice is still entirely and absolutely hers.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Finally, the agents of the Divine meddle in the plans of Infernal lords.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Tainted characters are designed for specific situations. Characters who struggle successfully against their destiny find that their creator cannot usually fashion an alternative situation to which the tainted person is perfectly suited. The tainted character loses the Tragic Life Flaw, but usually gains the Plagued by Supernatural Entity Flaw instead, as the demonic lord vents his spite on the character.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"tragic-life","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926072292,"modifiedTime":1730929087146,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"6gYd3WEaJtMiWKHM","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Blatant Magical Air","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">Only characters with a Magical Air or The Gift may take this Flaw.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">The character is especially disturbing to others, so much that they can barely tolerate its presence. The character suffers a –6 penalty to social actions, and is immediately hated and feared by members of the mundane population. This effect is the same as the Blatant Gift, and a character may not have both Flaws.</span></p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"blatant-magical-air","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918256212,"modifiedTime":1730929087161,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"6jT0LmwrG4zAaqo5","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Overconfident (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have a completely unshakable faith in your own abilities. You believe that you will always perform at, or slightly above, the peak of your abilities, and cannot imagine failure. If you actually botch, you come up with some rationalization as to what 'really' happened.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"overconfident-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"6pcoRWqKZd7KF4DS","sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Feud","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Your family is involved in a feud. The opposing family or families are roughly of equivalent strength to your family and its allies. You are liable to be ambushed or attacked by opposing clansmen, and your family expects you to join raids against your enemies.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"feud","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756700028,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"77gdSAnxVCavnevq","sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Abandoned Apprentice","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character was abandoned by his master midway through his Hermetic training. He knows Hermetic magic and can cast spells and enchant items like other magi. He is not a member of the Order of Hermes, however. </p><p>Some Tribunals rule that an apprentice has a year to find another parens before he is hunted down and slain like a Marched magus. Most Tribunals rule that abandoning an apprentice is a low crime, and if the character makes his situation known his parens may face legal action. </p><p>Decide at what age the character was abandoned. Create the character as a regular apprentice up until that age, and then give him experience points based on his age and other Virtues for his life past being abandoned. If the character knows the Parma Magica, he must join the Order or be slain. </p><p>Even if the character joins the Order, his background continues to cause problems for him.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"abandoned-apprentice","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729885070117,"modifiedTime":1730929087177,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"7G6T3bmUtRw53EK5","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Monstrous Blood","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character’s essential nature has been changed through exposure to the Magic realm, often because of a relationship to a magic being, which gives her true form unfortunate supernatural properties. This changes the character’s appearance enough that others can immediately recognize that there is something wrong about her, and people might say that she has tainted blood. The character is more resistant to age and receives a –1 bonus to all Aging rolls, and may learn Magic Lore during character creation.&nbsp;</p><p>However, the character also gains a minor physical deformity appropriate to the Magic being type that is associated with the character’s background. Some examples are below, or you can make up your own.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Magic Animal: </strong>The character has a physical feature normally associated with animals, such as wings, scales, gills, sharp teeth, or claws. These are not usable by the character, and give a –3 penalty to appropriate activities (such as running or climbing) as these deformities get in the way.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Magic Human: </strong>The character must decrease one of his Characteristics by 1, but not below –3. This might be Strength or Stamina to represent weakened blood, or Presence to indicate a dowdy appearance. The character also has a poor Reputation of level 3 among other magic beings.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Magic Spirit: </strong>The character has a mental block against many activities that are not supernatural, possibly due to a noticeable difficulty with retaining memories. Subtract 3 from all of the character’s Intelligence and Perception rolls that do not involve a Supernatural Ability or Art.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Magic Thing: </strong>The character has a constant Lesser Power that is mostly detrimental to it in some way, such as a ward that prevents it from picking up wooden objects, or that causes books it touches to burst into flame. The effect normally occurs involuntarily, but the character can spend a Confidence Point to prevent it from triggering.&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"monstrous-blood","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730528195169,"modifiedTime":1730929087190,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"7i3XkrbmnVO0GEct","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Pious (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are a fervent follower of your religion. You avoid the things it prohibits, and enthusiastically do the things it commands.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"pious-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928999664,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"7lv6LxpF5nIKEWeu","sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Difficult Underlings","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You may only take this Story Hook if your character has, and will keep, underlings of some sort or another. No matter how many people you fire, or how carefully you vet new candidates, your underlings always cause problems for you. The nature of the problems may change, but you are repeatedly drawn into dealing with the trouble they have caused. If other people give the same underlings orders, they have no problem. It’s not them, it’s you.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"difficult-underlings","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730785282072,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"7lzX2KAmqOgxXHQn","sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Meddler (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You want to fix other peoples’ lives: arrange matches, teach children to sew “properly,” or tend the sick. You waste a lot of time and energy on such endeavors, and people usually resent it.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"meddler-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756700101,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"84GN2hbcAKLuDhdR","sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Higher Purpose - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Let others concern themselves with petty matters, you have a nobler goal. This purpose should be altruistic, like freeing an oppressed people or bringing peace between the Order of Hermes and society.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"higher-purpose","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730455526556,"modifiedTime":1730925316113,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"8l2qrPY50F8rGDRp","sort":150000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Warped Senses","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character has become overly sensitive to environmental conditions, which affects his behavior in certain uncommon circumstances. Some examples include:</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><strong>Sensitive (Sense):</strong> One of your senses is so sensitive that it is overwhelmed under circumstances that others find normal. If it is sight, normal daylight dazzles you. If it is hearing, sounds above normal speaking volume hurt your ears. If it is taste, only bland food is tolerable. If it is smell, strong odors, good or bad, are nauseating. You suffer a –2 penalty on all activities under relevant circumstances. (It is inadvisable to combine Sensitive Sight with Keen Vision, and Sensitive Hearing with Sharp Ears, and these are incompatible with Blind and Deaf, respectively.)</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><strong>Weak (Sense):</strong> One of your senses is so weak that it is useless under circumstances that others find normal. If it is sight, you can only see well in good illumination (e.g. broad daylight). If it is hearing, you can only hear sounds above normal speaking volume. If taste, only highly flavored food is palatable. If smell, you can only detect strong odors. You suffer a –2 penalty on all activities under relevant circumstances. (Weak Sight is incompatible with Sensitive Sight, Keen Vision, and Blind and you cannot take Weak Hearing with Sensitive Hearing, Sharp Ears, or Deaf.)</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><strong>Sensitive to Cold:</strong> You function normally at temperatures considerably above the norm for your part of the world. You lose 1 Fatigue level for every hour you spend in an environment two steps or more below your accustomed conditions on the Environmental Temperatures chart (see sidebar). Your responses to heat are reduced in intensity by 2 (page @@).</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><strong>Sensitive to Heat:</strong> You function normally at temperatures considerably below the norm for your part of the world. You lose 1 Fatigue level for every hour you spend in an environment two steps or more above your habituated conditions on the Environmental Temperatures chart (see page @@). Your response to ice is reduced in intensity to 0 (page @@).</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This is a common Flaw for characters who become Warped by a strong magic environment.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"warped-senses","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730928539306,"modifiedTime":1730929087202,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"8s1I73DhGbG3loxC","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Stigmatic Catalyst","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character’s presence sometimes causes symbolic marks to appear on the bodies of people without Magic Resistance nearby. The character cannot control this process, but may make Intelligence + Enigmatic Wisdom rolls against an Ease Factor of 6 to tell those so afflicted what form of spiritual purification they must undergo for the stigma to disappear. Characters who are stigmatized may have a hostile reaction if they realize the source of the stigmata. This Flaw is normally found among magi of House Criamon, and magi of that House would be interested in any other character who manifested it.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"stigmatic-catalyst","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922752116,"modifiedTime":1730929087216,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"9GCkd8QkqgWUqyQk","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Arthritis","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Your joints are stiff and often painful, making almost any prolonged movement difficult. You are at –3 to rolls involving repetitive movement, sustained over time. Occasionally, the pain is so great that you are seriously disabled. On any movement or combat botch, one of your joints may “lock up,” making the limb effectively useless (–6 to all rolls involving it) until you have a chance to rest it for a day or two.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"arthritis","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"9Q86ADdJOOOzSQZE","sort":3200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Branded Criminal","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_da50amwz3qe","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>As punishment for some crime in your past, a mark has been burned into your cheek. This ad</p><p>versely affects your ability to function in society. You may not take the Wealthy Virtue, but you may take Martial Abilities at character creation. You may choose not to take such abilities, if your crime was not violent.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"branded-criminal","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756700158,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"49M5jwoqSphEsyDt","_id":"9SdR95grLkZYj5dD","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Dutybound","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You adhere to a restrictive code of conduct that forbids certain behavior, probably including prohibitions against lying, killing prisoners, stealing, and other occasionally useful actions. You follow this code out of guilt or fear rather than high-flown moral standards, and may spend more time justifying yourself than keeping your conduct pure.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"dutybound","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"9hBZ5PTKhaHE59kh","sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Suppressed Gift","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character has The Gift but cannot access its power, having temporarily lost his magical ability through mishap or some other misfortune. While the Gift is suppressed, the character cannot perform Hermetic magic, improve his Arts, or perform the Parma Magica. His Arts do provide him with Magic Resistance and he continues to suffer the negative social penalties of The Gift. Such a character may still use Supernatural Virtues and Abilities. He may be a member of the Order of Hermes, depending on when his Gift was suppressed.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">How The Gift returns should be decided by the storyguide. Examples are surviving a laboratory disaster while assisting another magus (perhaps that was how Suppressed Gift was gained), comprehending a Temporary Twilight while in a powerful regio, visiting the Magic Realm and succeeding in some task, or undergoing a year’s instruction from an elder dragon.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The troupe should consider carefully how the character will fit into the saga. If he replaces a player’s magus, he has a very serious Flaw. If he replaces a companion, he will become much more powerful when the Story Flaw is resolved. Either approach can work, with care.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"suppressed-gift","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922975464,"modifiedTime":1730929087228,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"A2P3JZlmEVLVzlBA","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Corrupted Arts","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character has studied one of the Hermetic Arts from a corrupted source. Use of a corrupted Art for a selfish or sinful action receives a +3 bonus to the character’s Casting Total. Succeeding in a roll because of this bonus (that is, when without it the roll would have failed) means he immediately acquires 5 experience points in that Art. However, uses of the Art that are neutral or selfless receive a –3 penalty, and if you fail the roll because of this penalty, he immediately loses 5 experience points in the Art.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Any use of a corrupted Art taints the character’s magic, causing it to appear unholy. You may only take this Flaw once, though it can affect multiple Arts.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"corrupted-arts","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729923624914,"modifiedTime":1730929087241,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"AHn3JftIAaQ3SSHk","sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Impious Friend","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A minor demon poses as a friend of the character. The demon takes a pleasant form but is usually invisible to anyone, other than its charge, who lacks appropriate supernatural abilities. Many of these demons are introduced to the tainted people they will defend and control during infancy. They become childhood playmates.&nbsp;</p><p>The tainted person has not bargained for the services of the demon. Instead, the character receives the services of his friend as part of its master’s plan to guide the character toward a tragic destiny. If the demon feels the character’s life is threatened, it may seek additional assistance from its master. The tainted person believes the demon wishes only the best for him. Many are ignorant of the demon’s true shape.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"impious-friend","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730457739974,"modifiedTime":1730929087255,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"BDeGSECPp1dstnjL","sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Infamous","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>People know you well and curse you in their prayers. You have a level 4 bad Reputation, specifying the horrible deeds that earned you such ill will.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"infamous","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"BO3XZhRJvnYzMXq3","sort":3300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Deficient Technique","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>All totals, including Lab and Casting totals, including a particular Technique are halved. Advancement Totals are not halved. Experience points required are based on the actual value of the Technique, before halving.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"deficient-technique","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730757370397,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"Bn3r6QkMvKGi2Vpi","sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Evil Destiny","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The Infernal realm has taken an interest in the character, but he does not know how or why. Perhaps one of his Powers is actually Infernal, or demons are plotting against him, or he is convinced that he is being stalked by something evil. </p><p>He cannot discuss this openly for fear that he will be accused of infernalism, but must be always on his guard against the dark forces that he knows will come for him one day. </p><p>The storyguide will use this Flaw to subtly work the Infernal realm into your character, leaving you unaware of the specifics. You might have other Flaws that relate to the Infernal, but not (yet) know what they are, such as Corrupted Abilities. The character could also simply be Plagued by Demons or Susceptible to the Infernal. Through the course of the story you may eventually discover what his Flaw is, but until then you are only haunted with the knowledge that something about him is not right.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"evil-destiny","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013285599,"modifiedTime":1730929087268,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"CALr6mU9FH4WUaGS","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Evil Eye","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You character bears the Evil Eye, the uncontrolled potential to bring harm to others around her. Characters making stress rolls in her presence are subject to an additional botch die. Characters may protect themselves through the use of an amulet or a ritual, decided upon by the troupe, which does not need to be magical or supernatural in nature. A Magic Resistance of 0 or more, including the effect of the Aegis of the Hearth, is also sufficient to guard against this effect.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"evil-eye","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013332579,"modifiedTime":1730929087282,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"CB4llTkFbSW1JV2t","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Pious (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are a fervent follower of your religion. You avoid the things it prohibits, and enthusiastically do the things it commands.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"pious-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730929008135,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"CFtyK6svM9eJ2GdS","sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Hermetic Patron","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You must be a Redcap or magus to take this Flaw.</p><p>You are watched over by an older magus or a more established Redcap, who considers you his charge and helps you out from time to time. This patron must be an NPC. Because of your special relationship, he is willing to do additional favors for you that cost him little, such as casting spells on you, lending you magic items, allowing you access to his books, providing you with mundane materials, supporting you financially for a season or two, or even adopting you into his House. However, in return he will expect special attention from you, and may periodically send you on missions or assign you important tasks.</p><p>You may take this Flaw with a large group of magi as your patrons, though the more numerous your benefactors, the more you will be expected to do for them.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"hermetic-patron","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730455466694,"modifiedTime":1730929087295,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"CnetuzlnRRY4FGyK","sort":6100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Flawed Parma Magica","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Your Parma Magica is defective and provides only half the normal Magic Resistance against a certain Form. You may purchase this Flaw more than once for different Forms.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"flawed-parma-magica","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756700298,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"D1g0Yew88b2Lglhj","sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Reckless - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You tend not to notice that situations are threatening, and certainly do not stop to consider whether they might be. You just go ahead and charge right in.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"reckless","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730921535783,"modifiedTime":1730929029751,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"D27YwH462hztiEua","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Necessary Condition","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>In order for your magic to work, you must perform a specific action while casting any spell. This should be something simple, such as singing or spinning around three times. If you cannot perform the action, you cannot cast spells at all.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"necessary-condition","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730785656523,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"D71ur9xyPhfM2FWw","sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weak-willed","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You look to others for guidance rather than to yourself. What you need more than anything else is to find someone you can trust.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"weak-willed","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730929050585,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"DUS6aMXvNqkpYtL2","sort":2200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Prohibition","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have had a Conditional Curse (also known as a \"Geas\") cast upon you and must obey the restrictions of your prohibition or be penalized by the curse. If you fail to adhere to the restrictions, you will suffer the curse in full force. The troupe must agree on both the restriction, and the curse that strikes you if you break it.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"prohibition","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"DagQlDqy2eLxgOiK","sort":2300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Indiscreet","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are unable to keep a secret. You must tell all to the first interested party you meet in an effort to be helpful or to demonstrate that you are in-the-know, unless you succeed on an Intelligence-based stress roll against an Ease Factor of 9. If you botch, you may have to be physically restrained by your companions from answering any questions put to you for the remainder of the encounter.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"indiscreet","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756700355,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"DcX2UiXnUXk52wtD","sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Hobbled","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Both of the character’s legs are severely damaged. She may not walk unless assisted by crutches or other devices, with which she can only move a mere half mile per hour. Any roll that requires moving quickly is penalized by –9. Her Dodge and other combat rolls are penalized by –6, and you roll double the normal botch dice in combat situations.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"hobbled","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730455594725,"modifiedTime":1730929087311,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Duld4K4cTLAY2Tyh","sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Outcast","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_da50amwz3qe","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have the rough task of making it on your own-normal society rejects you and you are not attached to a covenant. Perhaps you have a magical nature, a supernatural background, some disfigurement, or a tremendous scandal in your past. You may not take the Wealthy Virtue.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"outcast","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756700386,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"49M5jwoqSphEsyDt","_id":"E9VZcge3x4DLh6j2","sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Restricted Power","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This Flaw limits the use of a supernatural power that can normally be used at will, such as those granted by the Focus Power, Greater Power, Lesser Power, Personal Power, and Ritual Power Virtues. The character must perform some special ceremony to activate it, such as drawing symbols on the ground or gesturing and chanting like a magus, or else the power only functions on a limited class of targets (such as men, wolves, sounds, or sand) or in specific circumstances (like at night, under water, when touching iron, or after singing a song). This Flaw may be taken once for each power the character possesses.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"restricted-power","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730921797776,"modifiedTime":1730929087325,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"EJVDpiDmUMu7dmBy","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Flawed Powers","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character must have at least one Major Supernatural Virtue to take this Flaw. The character’s supernatural powers are limited or restricted in some fashion. She suffers the effects of a Major Hermetic Flaw (commonly Restriction or Necessary Condition), but it is applied to her Supernatural Virtues rather than to her Hermetic magic (if any). Any Flaw that is only appropriate to Hermetic Magic (for example, Deficient Technique or Unstructured Caster) cannot be taken with this Flaw. Note that the restriction on the supernatural power is not a separate Major Flaw: this Minor Flaw represents the fact that a Major Supernatural Virtue is less central to a character’s activities than Hermetic magic is to a magus.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"compulsion-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014448737,"modifiedTime":1730756700400,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","_id":"ELeGYJIPsJQLQzOw","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weak Characteristics","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have three fewer points to spend buying Characteristics than most characters. You may take this Flaw twice, leaving you with only one point to spend.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"weak-characteristics","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928590264,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"EmkMJ7Z8xkyxJE4k","sort":3400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"True Love (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You have found the one person meant for you in all of creation, and the bond between the two of you cannot be sundered. Whenever you are suffering, in danger, or dejected, the thought of your love will give you strength to persevere. In dire need, he may even come to rescue you. More often, he will be in trouble and need rescuing. If any enchantment keeps you from your true love's side, the power of your devotion can probably break it. Your love is higher than mortal magic, and no magic can make you hate your love, or make you truly betray him. Your True Love must be a non-player character. To have another player character as your True Love, see the True Love Virtue on page @@.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This Story Hook may be renamed 'True Friend' to cover characters with whom you are very closely linked, but not in a romantic way.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">If the True Love is significantly weaker than the player character, and not able to provide useful assistance in most cases, this is a Major Flaw. If the True Love is competent, equal to or better than the player character, then this is only a Minor Flaw. The True Love may need rescuing occasionally, but more often she will involve the player character in her plans.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"true-love-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730926096948,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","_id":"EskmkOhq3c7909oI","sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Motion Sickness","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Riding a horse, in a cart, or sailing on a ship makes you violently ill. When not traveling on foot, you suffer double the fatigue loss on long journeys, with a minimum loss of two Fatigue levels. Violent jostling over a period of a few hours could conceivably lead to unconsciousness.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"motion-sickness","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"EsqiddgW4ASze7QD","sort":3500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Avaricious - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You want money, lots of money. When you have it, you do not spend it, but hoard it so that you can count it. You can be avaricious about physical things other than money, such as books or raw vis. In this case, you do not use the things you hoard, nor do you allow others to use them.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"avaricious-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"FHX1tsMxnqZwtjzN","sort":2400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Feral Scent","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">Perhaps due to his beast blood or feral upbringing, the character has the strong natural smell of a wild animal. Humans tend to avoid being too close to him, and may be on edge in his vicinity without knowing why. He may well spook domesticated animals if he surprises them. He suffers a –1 penalty to social interactions (which stacks with the penalties imposed by The Gift, if he has it), and develops a negative Reputation of Unclean at level 2. However, if he has Initiated the Sensory Magic Mystery (described in <em>Houses of Hermes: Mystery Cults,</em> page 27), any spells he casts with a Scent Target have twice their normal area of effect.</span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"feral-scent","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013989284,"modifiedTime":1730929087339,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"FOPpbdCaXBO06ETj","sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Disfigured","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A visible disfigurement makes you ugly and easy to recognize. Presence rolls that involve good looks and gaining respect from most people are at –3. You probably have a cruel nickname that refers to your unfortunate appearance. You might have a large, visible burn scar, or an enlarged and deformed eye (an ‘evil eye’), or even be albino.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"disfigured","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"FjvHd5kQrX2zv5WF","sort":3600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Witch Marks","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character has minor disfigurements that those skilled in folk lore recognize as belonging to diabolists. These marks can be hidden with clothing. Characters who are thought of as witches are blamed for misfortunes and may be hounded from towns or killed.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"witch-marks","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730928928985,"modifiedTime":1730929087351,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"FsofwKyuaitigXHx","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Jinxed","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character is a magnet for any bad luck. He is not personally the cause of the bad luck, and so need not roll any extra botch dice or suffer any penalty to die rolls. However, whenever chance determines who will be affected by misfortune, the odds are biased against him to be the one affected. For example, if it has been determined that a rope used for climbing will break, it is more likely to do so when the jinxed character makes the climb. If determining when the bandits will attack the camp at night, it is more likely to happen right at the moment when the character is relieving himself. If the storyguide is rolling dice to determine the target of a random event, a jinxed character should be affected half of the time, and his comrades between them the other half. His bad luck does not tend to spill over onto others; in fact, other characters may prefer to keep him around to deflect any bad luck from themselves.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"jinxed","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730464749914,"modifiedTime":1730929087365,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"GSWUrR56n923BnS1","sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Optmistic (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are convinced that everything will turn out for the best. This is not overconfidence, as you accept that you might well fail. Even if you do, however, you are sure that circumstances will mean that everything works to your benefit.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"optmistic-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925487050,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"GSnqweqwNbXIod28","sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Deficient Form","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Almost all totals (including Casting Totals and Lab Totals, but excluding Magic Resistance) to which a particular Form is added are halved. Advancement Totals are not halved. Experience points required are based on the actual value of the Technique, before halving.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"deficient-form","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758502615,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"H3fSPgvMxD7SpW1o","sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Poor Concentration","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">While the character may have a mind that is quick to make decisions, he has a short attention span. The character has a –3 penalty to Concentration rolls.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"poor-concentration","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730919231175,"modifiedTime":1730929087379,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"HCL0je9PBeeDSJzn","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Secretive","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character is prone to keeping secrets from his sodales. He rarely explains what he is doing or why he is doing it, which can frustrate those around him.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"higher-purpose","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922049046,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"HFRo3XV5BICI4I9y","sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Hunger for (Form) Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character has been repeatedly exposed to magic and has thus become dependent upon magic to survive. The character must consume 1 pawn of vis each season, corresponding to the Form that it has been mostly exposed to. If the character is unable to consume a pawn of vis in a season, it loses a Long-Term Fatigue Level that cannot be regained until a pawn of the appropriate vis is consumed. For example, a character that has Hunger for Ignem Magic and has not consumed a pawn of Ignem vis for a whole year will have lost 4 Long-Term Fatigue Levels, and so be Dazed with a –5 penalty to activities. If the character then consumes 1 pawn of Ignem vis, it will regain a Fatigue Level and become Tired after an hour has elapsed.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"hunger-for-form-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730457628271,"modifiedTime":1730929087395,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"HJIaPkOUiPZYRW7i","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Faerie Upbringing","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Perhaps you were abandoned by your true kin, and the faeries found you. Maybe your family actually lived in a faerie forest, or faeries took you as a babe. Though you are now back in human society, you feel at home with and have an enhanced understanding of faeries, magic, and other strange things. However, you find human society, including religion, bizarre. You may learn Faerie Lore at character generation.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"faerie-upbringing","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"HR9pHVRepCZDhuSX","sort":2500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Unnatural Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Because of the unreal and illusory nature of your magic, none of the character’s Creo rituals have a permanent effect. Wounds magically closed with <em>The Chirurgeon’s Healing Touch</em> (CrCo20), for example, reopen again as soon as he finishes casting the spell, as the magic truly lasts only a moment. He also cannot extract vis from an aura using Creo, since his version of that Art is too unstable for the vis to remain in a lasting physical form.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"unnatural-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926629969,"modifiedTime":1730929087408,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"HRtx9ABeP8cKnOT3","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Warped Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your magic is accompanied by some unpleasant side effect that always manifests itself the same way, but with increasing intensity according to the level of the spell. Examples include nearby items become hot or nearby plant matter becomes shriveled and wilted. This effect may cause trouble from time to time, but is usually just annoying.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"warped-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730927314886,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"Hl0Agiz67WhEAV2Q","sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Short-lived Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your spells do not last as long as they should. Spells that should last a year, last a moon; those of a moon, only to the next sunrise or sundown; and those of a sun, merely Diameter. Diameter, Concentration, Ring, and Momentary spells are not affected.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"short-lived-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922289461,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"I7hrCji6YSCHBvcA","sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Low Self-esteem","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have a deflated opinion of your own selfworth. You begin the game with no Confidence Score, and never have any Confidence Points.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"low-self-esteem","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925496954,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","_id":"I9IMIqopDm2QodL6","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Greater Malediction","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xc1hyhkw51","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have been cursed by some supernatural power, in a way that greatly hinders you. The effects of the curse should be comparable to those of other Major Flaws. Indeed, almost any Flaw could be the result of a curse.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"greater-malediction","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756700575,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","_id":"I9pbOgTPsaIX4MGM","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Lesser Malediction","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xc1hyhkw51","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have been cursed by some supernatural power. The effects of the curse should be about as bad as other Minor General Flaws.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"lesser-malediction","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730464909312,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","_id":"IEtt9UA7vVadHplU","sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weak Spontaneous Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You may not exert yourself when casting spontaneous magic, so you always divide your Casting Score by five. In stressful conditions you must still roll a stress die to see if you botch, but the die roll does not add to your casting total. You may still use ceremonial casting.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This Flaw may be combined with Difficult Spontaneous Magic (page @@) to create a magus who cannot cast spontaneous magic at all.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"weak-spontaneous-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928803381,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"Igv2QJa0ZUwDMjyD","sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Apostate","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">You have converted from one faith to another or from one set of beliefs to another. You have a bad Reputation at 4 among members of your previous faith, and you may receive some slight distrust from your new faith as well, depending upon how sincere your conversion seems.</span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"apostate","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729917822385,"modifiedTime":1730929087422,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"IltfRtfSDA6GgImu","sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Incomprehensible","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are almost completely unable to convey the knowledge and understanding that you have. Anyone trying to learn from you or from a book you have written must halve their Advancement Total (or Lab Total, if you are a magus and have written Lab Texts on some spells or enchanted items). If you are a magus teaching spells, halve all applicable Lab Totals, both yours and the student’s.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"incomprehensible","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"IzC8E9hoKCnBs3bR","sort":3700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Clumsy","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are not very graceful and tend to drop things — you are at –3 in all related rolls. Furthermore, roll an extra botch die when taking actions related to Dexterity. Roleplay your clumsiness.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"clumsy","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"JMKSpg7bTCIcvud9","sort":3800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Rebellious - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You react adversely to any attempt to impose authority over you, and work against those who are in command. You do not necessarily have any desire to be a leader yourself, but you don’t like to be pushed around.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"higher-purpose","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730921367623,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"JSxg69Sy8OeH1Rdb","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Poor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are a poor member of your social class. You must work three seasons per year in order to make ends meet, and can afford only the necessities of life, as measured by your status. This also means that you have one fewer season available for any form of advancement other than exposure, which is a major hindrance. You cannot take this Flaw if you are supported by the covenant. In particular, this Flaw is not available to magi.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"poor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925504573,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","_id":"JTAGKI9a7v8YBsio","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Poor Eyesight","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Bleary vision impedes your performance. Rolls involving sight, including rolls to attack and defend, are at –3. New environments are disorienting and perhaps frightening for you. This Flaw can be combined with Missing Eye (above), but the penalties are cumulative.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"poor-eyesight","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"Jfm1wqI2U0KnFA8m","sort":3900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Unpredictable Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You always roll a stress die when using magic, even if completely relaxed. If you choose to cast a spontaneous spell without expending fatigue, you must still roll to check for a botch, although the roll does not add to your Casting Total. Even if you have mastered a spell, you must always roll at least one botch die.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"unpredictable-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730926673682,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"K7X0REkRf7eh4Mah","sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Disorientating Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>After casting a spell, you must spend a round doing nothing but recovering your mental faculties.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"disorientating-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756700665,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"KOgFadAbWyBoYmqk","sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Generous (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You willingly give away your property to anyone who expresses a desire for it, even if they are not particularly deserving. If something is very important, you might not give it to someone, but you will certainly share it.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"generous-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756700678,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"KV90k3EllulrZ5xc","sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Poor (characteristic)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You have an exceedingly bad Characteristic — lower one which is already –3 or lower by one point. Describe what it is about you that makes this obvious, such as a feeble stature, hideous visage, or slack-jawed stupidity. You may take this Flaw twice for a single Characteristic, lowering it to –5, and multiple times for different Characteristics.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"poor-characteristic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"KWrFxqwP2iZbVfzy","sort":4000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Heir","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have little power or wealth now, but you stand to inherit land and possibly money. You need do nothing special to remain in your position, but others may occasionally attempt to remove you from the line of succession — one way or another. When you finally win your inheritance you gain its responsibilities as well, so your freedom may be restricted.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"heir","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758110122,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","_id":"KgFvk6ryaJSitrKy","sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Flashbacks","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">When engaged in combat, or a similar violent and tense situation, the stress might trigger a flashback to the horrors of past battles, which left this character mentally scarred. The hallucinations seem so real that it is hard to avoid reacting to them. When an event appropriate for the Flashbacks occurs, roll a stress die against an Ease Factor of 9. On a failure, the character panics and reverts to his past nightmares. At the storyguide’s discretion, modifiers from –1 to –5 could apply, for things like full-scale battle, fires, or stampeding animals. In addition, add or subtract any relevant Personality Traits, depending on whether they might lessen or worsen the effects of this Flaw.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">Bear in mind that positive traits like loyal, reliable, law-abiding, or calm should be helpful in avoiding this affliction. Similarly, negative traits like selfish, angry, or corrupt subtract from the roll, making him more likely to succumb. Often, his actions hurt, embarrass, or offend comrades, employers, or other important people, and might have social repercussions. On a botch, he’ll get into real trouble — it could result in someone being seriously hurt or killed, in valuables being broken or in him failing in his duty at a critical time.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">For magi, this Flaw should not involve flashbacks to Twilight episodes, spell botches or laboratory disasters. Since most of these situations won’t get worse by applying a penalty to the rest of the scene, it won’t be enough of a Flaw. But magi can be affected by combat, house fires, or cave-ins just as much as other character types.</span></p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"flashbacks","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014249330,"modifiedTime":1730929087434,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"KjsETbClVHJvPvQA","sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Curse Of Venus","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are very attractive to people whom you do not wish to attract. People you detest keep getting crushes on you, and will not be dissuaded. Furthermore, you tend to fall in love with inappropriate people, and in inappropriate circumstances. Those people you are interested in tend to think you are vain and shallow.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"curse-of-venus","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730785239774,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"LXsbSXtGbeDtJvtX","sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Susceptibility To Divine Power","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are especially sensitive to the Dominion and suffer twice the normal penalties (such as spellcasting modifiers and botch dice) to your magic when in a Divine aura.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"susceptibility-to-divine-power","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730923104128,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"LcOGbLOqbYp02y6Y","sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Rector (Proctor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character is the representative leader of his faculty or nation at a university, depending on whether he is a master or a student. He is responsible for his colleagues’ behavior and is obliged to deal with their academic concerns. The character must have a Social Status Virtue dictating his place within the university. The character can expect to spend considerable time sorting out his fellows’ affairs.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"rector-proctor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730921612780,"modifiedTime":1730929087447,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"LqUpOB51iZaaMpX4","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Environmental Magic Condition","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>All of the character’s Casting and Lab Totals are halved in certain common conditions related to his environment, for example, whenever he is inside. Note that this should be significantly more restrictive than the Hermetic Flaw Deleterious Circumstances.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"environmental-magic-condition","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013186071,"modifiedTime":1730929087461,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"LyCkGkd7mikz8EIV","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Frail","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character is weak of build and easily hurt when undertaking physical activities. He has a –3 penalty to his Soak score.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"frail","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014854487,"modifiedTime":1730929087476,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Lyzn5HvlL2jBZ4VC","sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Susceptibility To Infernal Power","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are especially vulnerable to the dark powers. Whenever you enter an area of Infernal influence, you must make a Stamina roll equal to or greater than the aura rating or become ill (–1 on all rolls). You get only half your normal Magic Resistance score against infernal effects, though if someone else's Parma Magica is protecting you, it counts normally.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"susceptibility-to-infernal-power","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730923156584,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"MQtEd50b1X4R44l5","sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weak Enchanter","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Your Gift is ill attuned to creating enchanted devices. Halve your Lab Total whenever you create or investigate an enchanted item. If you have a Deficiency that counts as part of the Lab Total, apply the Deficiency first and then halve the remaining total.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"weak-enchanter","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928609055,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"Mm2Z3PWNUW3Eh4e0","sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Environmental Sensitivity","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character is unusually sensitive to an uncommon environmental feature, such as bad air, salt water, or extreme temperatures. Whenever the character is exposed to these conditions, he has a –3 penalty to his Stamina for any debilitation checks (page @@).</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"environmental-sensitivity","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013225756,"modifiedTime":1730929087489,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"N0Hj39V33njyz049","sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Visions (Supernatural)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xc1hyhkw51","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You often see images related to emotionally or magically laden events. A vision might be of the past, a possible future, or a distant occurrence, and is often symbolic or confusing. Visions usually come to you at quiet times or in places connected with a powerful emotional or magical event, such as the site of a patricide or diabolic sacrifice. Your visions may warn you of dangers to come, or get you involved in matters you would otherwise have avoided.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The visions come purely at the storyguide's discretion, and reveal only what he wants to reveal.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"visions-supernatural","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730929129486,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","_id":"NmQhK11JOgTJYgGC","sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Vulnerable Casting","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Some magi are better able to withstand the Fatigue loss of casting spells, and some less so. If a maga has this Flaw, then whenever she is about to lose Fatigue from casting a spell, she loses 1 more Fatigue level than normal. If the spell would have been cast without Fatigue loss, then she still loses no Fatigue.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">A maga may have, or acquire, this Flaw more than once, losing 1 extra Fatigue level for each level of this Flaw. If she has Vulnerable Casting (2), then she loses 2 extra Fatigue levels whenever she casts a fatiguing spell.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Magi of the Mercurian cults often succumb to this Flaw, but other magi may suffer from it, regardless of their affiliation.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The Flaw increases the severity of the Fatigue lost, in the exact manner of the existing Fatigue loss. Thus, if a maga casts a Formulaic spell, the Fatigue is short-term Fatigue, easily recovered, and if she runs out of Fatigue levels she is rendered unconscious, loss of extra Fatigue levels results in her being unconscious for one hour for each overflowing level, and so does the Fatigue from Vulnerable Casting. If, on the other hand, she casts a Ritual spell, then this is long-term Fatigue, and losing more Fatigue than she has remaining causes wounds, so the increased Fatigue of Vulnerable Casting does the same.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You may not start your character with both Vulnerable Casting and Withstand Casting, but the maga may acquire either in the course of play (from Initiation, Ordeals, or Twilight effects). In this case, apply the vulnerability first, then withstand the increased loss.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"vulnerable-casting","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730927132800,"modifiedTime":1730929087502,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"OAIEP8ki3Yxq8yK4","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Slothful","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are a self-proclaimed member of the Seekers, a loose organization of competitive magi searching for ancient magic and arcane artifacts. Much of your life is spent in pursuit of these items. Your interests may occasionally clash with other interests of your House or covenant. More details about the Seekers can be found on page 15 of <em>Houses of Hermes: True Lineages.</em></p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"higher-purpose","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922407237,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"OG4FvxamdcxrGz1B","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Depraved - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character seeks to undermine religion whenever possible, and generally tries to avoid the Dominion. He might sin in public, teach misinformation about the tenets of the faith, or show obvious disdain for holy things. He is not necessarily an infernalist; it could be that he simply despises organized religion, dislikes the Divine realm, or does not believe in God. He might even be persuaded to attend services, though he does not take any of it seriously and is likely to disrupt the ceremony with his discomfort and ignorance.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"depraved-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730012333054,"modifiedTime":1730929087517,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"OIkwLyXfEN4vwKL2","sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Fear","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are scared of something that you are likely to encounter fairly often. Its presence makes you edgy and very uncomfortable.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"fear","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"ONKegvWnmGg4rpzQ","sort":2600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Envious (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You believe that everyone has it better than you do, and that they don’t deserve their good fortune, while you do. Thus, you try to ruin their lives and take their goods for yourself. (This is not a good Flaw for a player character, as it is likely to lead to conflict with the other players.)</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"envious-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"OrDu7ZPKPqV3H16T","sort":2700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Tainted With Evil","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">An air of corruption surrounds you as a result of something you, your parents, or your ancestors did. Others naturally feel very ill at ease around you, and can easily grow to hate you. Gaining a positive Reputation is impossible. Magi do not react as strongly to this attribute as normal people.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"tainted-with-evil","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925878079,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"P5YOdXlQIcvqoTJT","sort":4100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Susceptibility To Faerie Power","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are especially susceptible to the fay and their magic. Whenever you enter a Faerie aura, you must make a Stamina roll equal to or greater than its aura rating to avoid becoming disoriented. In addition, your Magic Resistance score, including Parma Magica, against faerie effects is halved. If someone else uses their Parma Magica to protect you, their resistance is not affected and you benefit normally.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"susceptibility-to-faerie-power","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730923136668,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"PN5FfL29ukRLtwW2","sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Difficult Spontaneous Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Spontaneous magic is always an effort for you. You cannot cast Spontaneous spells without exerting yourself. However, when you do exert yourself, you cast spells as any other magus.</p><p>This Flaw may be combined with Weak Spontaneous Magic (page @@) to create a magus who cannot use Spontaneous magic at all.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"difficult-spontaneous-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758529464,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"Pd60aIt2D8dTcpQ9","sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Warped by Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character’s adventures have exposed him to powerful magical forces that have left a mark on him. He has five Warping Points and a Warping Score of 1, including a Minor Flaw (which is not balanced by a Virtue) that somehow reflects the source of the Warping. His encounters allow you to spend experience points on Magic Lore during character creation. A magus may take this Flaw to represent Warping gained before his apprenticeship. With the permission of the troupe, this Flaw may be modified to represent Warping from other Realms.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"warped-by-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730927296756,"modifiedTime":1730929087532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"PhtssOO8iuJPc3Yc","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Follower","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character is a follower, not a leader. He rarely takes the initiative, but is usually happy to follow the direction of a forthright and decisive person. If he finds a leader, he tends to stick with her.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"follower","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014647094,"modifiedTime":1730929087544,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"Q4dzKWpaz1LtOTOz","sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Ambitious - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You want to be the most successful or powerful person in the world in some respect. You will not be distracted into doing things that do not contribute to your ambition, and are very eager to do things that advance it.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"ambitious-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756960097,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"QbffNQHPSSnMqGpU","sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Night Terrors","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This character is plagued far too often by horrible nightmares and fits of screaming in his sleep. The character must make a Stress Roll against an Ease Factor of 9 in order to avoid suffering terrors. The storyguide may call for modifiers of –1 to –3 if he has faced eerie or terrifying events recently, like meeting a demon or battling the undead.&nbsp;</p><p>Suffering from terrors means that the character wakes up often and in a panic during the night. Situations might occur where he overreacts or reacts in unfortunate ways, if forced awake during such nights. The morning leaves him with a Long Term Fatigue Level lost. These Long Term Fatigue Levels are cumulative, so several bad nights leave him in bad shape. Subtract the character’s Fatigue penalty from the Ease Factor to avoid night terrors, to represent how a truly exhausted victim will at some point sleep through the nightmares due to sheer exhaustion. If a night of terrors renders the character Unconscious, he slips into deep, dreamless sleep. He sleeps for an entire day and night, and wakes up at Winded, ending the string of Night Terrors. A character with this Flaw may not also take the Sleep Disorder Flaw&nbsp;</p><p>This Flaw normally makes seasonal Laboratory work impossible, and so is not suitable for magi.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"night-terrors","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730528395173,"modifiedTime":1730929087558,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"QwTfhokzBksY7doX","sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Fluctuating Fortune","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character’s finances rise and fall like the tide, regardless of how successful he is or what preventative measures he takes. He is considered to have the Wealthy Virtue one year, followed by the Poor Flaw the next. Besides monetary concerns, this means that the character will have to only work one season in one year, followed by a year in which he has to work three, all to maintain his livelihood. This cycle of feast and famine continues throughout the character’s life, always in opposition to his financial desires. When he needs money most, he has none, and has an abundance of funds when they are superfluous. </p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"fluctuating-fortune","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014527945,"modifiedTime":1730929087571,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","_id":"R43vnp43LUvWa8hD","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Sheltered Upbringing","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You grew up completely separated from society, knowing only your parents or mentor. Recently you have been introduced to a wondrous new world of strangers, and you are overwhelmed. Depending on your personality, you might react with contempt, fear, or wonder. You are unable to function normally because you cannot understand most human customs. You may not take Bargain, Charm, Etiquette, Folk Ken, Guile, Intrigue, or Leadership as beginning Abilities, but you may learn them in play.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"sheltered-upbringing","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"RGEyXtA7o15zmdRD","sort":2800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Outlaw Leader","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_da50amwz3qe","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You command a small group (three to six persons) of outlaws. Your followers look up to you and do what you tell them — within reason. However, you must occasionally stick up for the group or one of its members, as well as provide for them. You often have to deal with challenges to your leadership in one form or another. You are well known as an outlaw in the local area, with a Reputation level of 3. You are actively sought by the local lord, sheriff, or other such official. You may take Martial Abilities at character generation. Grogs may not take this Flaw.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"outlaw-leader","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756700953,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"49M5jwoqSphEsyDt","_id":"RZ2tetfPJzUk7noo","sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Surgical Empiricus","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You are a chirurgeon by trade, but have never received a wide grounding in the subject; rather your training has focused on only a single aspect of Chirurgy. Pick a type of surgery as your specialization in that Ability (couching cataracts, removal of stones, bone-setting, etc.). When performing this type of surgery, you get the usual +1 bonus to your roll, but when trying to employ any other application of Chirurgy, you must halve your score in Chirurgy due to your inexperience. It is likely that you travel to get enough clientele for your practice, but can usually earn a good living.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"surgical-empiricus","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"49M5jwoqSphEsyDt","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730923027115,"modifiedTime":1730929087584,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Riy2w4DQaWxQVEJd","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Brutal Artist","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This Flaw is only available to magi of House Jerbiton. The magus creates and enjoys art that is ugly, according to his Housemates. He suffers a –3 penalty on social rolls with Jerbiton magi, and cannot develop a positive Reputation in the House, because his mind is so obviously disturbed. This restricts his involvement in the leagues (see <em>Houses of Hermes: Societates,</em> page 53). Over time, the character might convince his sodales that his work is not ugly, but this requires stories, much as removing any other Flaw.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"brutal-artist","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918834747,"modifiedTime":1730929087597,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"SD2niPeqxwmVYN2a","sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Generous (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You willingly give away your property to anyone who expresses a desire for it, even if they are not particularly deserving. If something is very important, you might not give it to someone, but you will certainly share it.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"generous-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"SeBKIjPNrsvarpUO","sort":2900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Fish Out of Water (Terrain)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">This character has an affinity with one type of terrain, whether this is at sea, in the woods, the rolling hills, or in the urban landscape of towns and cities, and feels uncomfortable and awkward when away from where he wants to be. The character suffers a –1 penalty to all stress rolls taken outside of their favored terrain and also rolls one more botch dice than normal in those situations.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">Appropriate areas may be Cities & Towns, Villages, Rivers, The Sea, Mountains, Woodland, Desert, etc.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">This Flaw may only be taken once, because taking it more than once makes it less serious, rather than more.</span></p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"fish-out-of-water-terrain","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014210592,"modifiedTime":1730929087611,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"SknACfON3zfowM6t","sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Inscribed Shadow","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character’s stigmata are reflected by glowing symbols in the character’s shadow. This causes alarm among non-magicians and makes the character’s stigmata extremely easy for other Criamon magi to read (+3 on all rolls). The shadow’s glowing symbols do not vanish when there is insufficient light to form a shadow — they burn brighter. Characters who use magic to hide their stigmata are not acting aptly. Only characters with stigmata may have this Flaw, which normally means that they must be magi of House Criamon.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"inscribed-shadow","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730458045804,"modifiedTime":1730929087625,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"T4SqU96WZn1YPC1k","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Painful Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Casting spells causes you to suffer the equivalent of one Fatigue level in pain for each spell you cast. This reduces all your actions by the appropriate Fatigue penalty, which is cumulative with any from actual fatigue or injuries (though you do not suffer any physical damage from pain). You recover these \"pain levels\" just like Fatigue levels.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"painful-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730919042777,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"TAGxZGdlArfltL4v","sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Bound to (Role) Role","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">This character is physically bonded to some form of device, whether through a mystic event, long years of exposure and warping, or the ministrations of an experimental magus. The degree of the bonding is for the troupe to define, but the bonding may be physical, such as a locksmith whose fingers are picks, files, and keys, or mystical, such as a watchman who is confined to his watch tower as though contained by an unbreakable ward.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">The manner of this bonding determines the kind of life that the character may live. A watchman unable to leave his tower may make it his home, while a coachman who has become part of his coach cannot survive for long once separated from it.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">If separated from the bonded device or place in any way, the character must make deprivation checks as though deprived of food (i.e., a check every three days). The effects of this are canceled if the character is brought into contact with the device or returned to his bound place, at which point they rebond.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">This Flaw also includes the effects of the Unaging Virtue, but the character’s apparent age advances in line with their physical age. Role-Bound characters retain the need to sleep and breathe and those not physically bonded to a device, such as those bound to a place, retain their other physical needs.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">This Flaw may originate from any of the Supernatural Realms: a magical origin might represent the expression of an Essential Trait, a faerie origin could show that the character occupies an archetypal role, ready to play his part in the wider story, while divine and infernal origins may represent eternal punishment on Earth.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">This Flaw may only be taken by grogs and is suitable for the <em>Warping to a Pattern</em> Minor Site Hook presented in <em>Covenants</em>, page 11.</span></p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"bound-to-role-role","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918526659,"modifiedTime":1730929087639,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"UgWpAHWhLVomBzdg","sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Visions (Story)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"","source":"ArM5","page":60,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"visions-story"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"12.324","createdTime":1662235751535,"modifiedTime":1696141994914,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru","compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null},"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","_id":"VMdxfI9f4ORRb61f","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Restriction","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You cannot cast spells at all under certain uncommon conditions. These might refer to your state, such as touching the earth directly or having no beard, or to the target, such as birds or glass, or to your location when you use the magic, such as on a small boat or in a storm. The Restriction also applies to effects generated by any enchanted items you create. Spells cast remain in effect even if the Restriction comes into play. Thus, if your Restriction is that you must not have a beard, you cast a spell with Year duration, and then grow a beard, the spell does not fail.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"restriction","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925512925,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"VSbWdtS4fdKdY8JD","sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Driven (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have some goal which you are determined to bring about. This has to be the sort of big goal that could shape an entire life, but if you do accomplish it you will immediately turn to a new project.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"driven-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"VXGi8TsLwFFbuvKV","sort":3000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Slow Caster","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your magic requires more time to prepare and execute than that of other magi. Your Formulaic spells take two rounds to cast; Spontaneous spells also take two rounds unless you fast-cast, in which case they take one round casting time. Fast-cast Mastered spells also take the normal one-round time. You can still cast Muto Vim spells on your own spells, but the casting process takes longer. Ritual spells and ceremonial castings are performed as normal, since all magi must cast them slowly and carefully.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"slow-caster","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922431803,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"VbcljlapH0Ws8rzD","sort":2200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weakness","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have a soft spot for some sort of object or person. In the face of this, all else is unimportant: promises are forgotten, duties neglected, and common sense cast to the winds. Examples include poets and storytellers, food, flattery, or a pretty face.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"weakness","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928859582,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"Vd8FH0D7eMDbLtYy","sort":3100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Overconfident (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have a completely unshakable faith in your own abilities. You believe that you will always perform at, or slightly above, the peak of your abilities, and cannot imagine failure. If you actually botch, you come up with some rationalization as to what 'really' happened.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"overconfident-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756701085,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"VpF0ceE7aDloJ4Nc","sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Mistaken Identity","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Someone, who looks exactly like you and whom you and your companions will most likely never meet, lives near you, and is responsible for an ongoing variety of violent, illegal, obscene, or embarrassing acts. You often have to explain who you are, and sometimes have to deal with the consequences of the other person’s acts.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"mistaken-identity","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756701098,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"VqOfOwYRhlElmuoX","sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Continence","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You do not engage in sexual activity. This may be due to a vow of celibacy, or simply personal choice.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"continence","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"VrOyrxzg6xgFVSSe","sort":3200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Demonic Familiar","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character is bound to a famulus, a familiar demon that possesses an animal and can lend the character its senses, or mask the evil taint of her Powers. This demonic familiar is not loyal to the character or concerned about her well-being, and often has its own goals and needs. The character may occasionally need to bargain with it or even threaten it to receive its aid.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">At the storyguide’s discretion, this Flaw may be taken to represent other sorts of demons with which the character has a close relationship, such as a warder, teacher, or paramour. The more powerful the demon, the more the character will be expected to do to earn its assistance, and the less involved it will be with her on a daily basis.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"demonic-familiar","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729926223190,"modifiedTime":1730929087652,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"W5AKClN2a83TOHAE","sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Unbaptized","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are a Christian who has never been baptized for whatever reason, perhaps because you have some kind of supernatural background that might be undone by the ceremony — many magi believe that baptism impairs The Gift. Your faith is important enough to you that you still strive to be virtuous and attend Mass, though you do not benefit from the sacraments. Most common people who discover this fear and avoid you.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"unbaptized","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926249996,"modifiedTime":1730929087666,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"WHBIDtcu61nLRTqn","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Tzadik Nistar","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your character is one of the Tzadikim Nistarim, one of the 36 hidden righteous upon which the continuation of the world relies. She is destined to face a moment of moral decision, where she and the world through her will be tested. This moment could be small and personal, or it require a very public act. The result of failing in her test has immediate consequences defined by the storyguide. The Dominion may fall in her community or in the place of her moral failure; the Infernal may claim a new soul; or a whole region may face severe hardship until she puts right her failure. Although this is a Jewish tradition, a character need not be Jewish to take this Flaw. She may suspect that she has been chosen as one of the 36, but she does not know in advance what her personal test will be, though it may be discovered by consulting with prophets and learned men.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"tzadik-nistar","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926193101,"modifiedTime":1730929087681,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"WHKb0GsxDqpKTgYg","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Lame","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>One of your legs is weakened, whether since birth or through some accident. You move slowly and clumsily. Your base speed is a mere one mile per hour, and anyone can outrun you. You suffer a –6 penalty on rolls involving moving quickly or with agility, –3 on Dodge, and –1 on other combat scores.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"lame","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"WJJL14ddzuUgc1ds","sort":4200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Bound Casting Tools","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The magus’s casting tools, as used by House Verditius, are so personal that they become lasting Arcane Connections to him. Regular casting tools remain as Arcane Connections for a few weeks, his last years.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"bound-casting-tools","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918382203,"modifiedTime":1730929087697,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"WLB1L5XQbhFx89ji","sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Black Sheep","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You come from a prestigious family, but you have somehow estranged yourself from your relatives. They have nothing to do with you, unless they wish to punish you somehow or make use of you. Those who resent your family’s power can take safe revenge by assaulting you. You begin the game with a bad Reputation of your choice at level 2, among those who respect your family.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"black-sheep","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730785231661,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"WPtBspG4NM7vgeZ3","sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
