{"name":"Unimaginative Learner","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[{"origin":"Item.XfALWkqBC4vvXu4H","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.activities.visStudy","value":"-3","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["activities"],"subtype":["visStudy"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Uniaginative learner","_id":"hFSBNsrS85NyJu9U","description":"","transfer":true,"statuses":[],"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null},"img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","type":"base","system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You have trouble figuring things out for yourself. Subtract 3 from rolls when you study from raw vis.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"unimaginative-learner","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730926469778,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"XfALWkqBC4vvXu4H","sort":2300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Disjointed Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You cannot use previous knowledge to help you with magic. You gain no benefit from knowing a spell that is similar to one you are learning or inventing, and you gain no enchantment bonuses from Techniques and Forms already invested in an item.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"disjointed-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758541979,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"Xx4FBMAE0ygRn122","sort":2400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Tainted Offspring","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character has a child who has been marked for great, but unpleasant, things by a powerful demon. The character must struggle not only with the servants the demon sends to subvert the child, but the child’s own tendency toward evil.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"tainted-offspring","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730925791481,"modifiedTime":1730929087711,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"YIWMcm0sVzsm8Yy4","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Deleterious Circumstances","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>All your magic totals, excluding Magic Resistance, are halved under certain uncommon circumstances. This can be your state, such as sitting or wet, the target of the magic, such as wild animals or iron, or the place where you are casting the magic, such as a city or high up a mountain.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"deleterious-circumstances","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758515481,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"YKp5cOGXrxlJ7L9I","sort":2500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Lecherous (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You seek sexual contact with as many people as possible. Note that you need not be any good at seduction; skill here merely changes the kinds of problems you encounter.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"lecherous-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"YgKsCM8JWuHlNMNJ","sort":3400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Gender Nonconforming - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You do not conform to the expected behavior for a person of the gender that your society would assign to you in the absence of social cues such as clothes and behavior. This may mean, for example, that you dress as a member of another gender, or that you structure your life in a way considered appropriate to another gender, or that you are sexually attracted to members of the same gender. It does not necessarily mean that you disagree about what your gender is, although it may. As a Minor Flaw, it does not normally cause you problems, whether because your society accepts your behavior, or because you can turn people who object into newts, or for some other reason. As a Major Flaw, it does cause you problems.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"gender-nonconforming-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730015075568,"modifiedTime":1730929087725,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"YhkkYHTmaV3wugom","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Vengeful Powers","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character has one or more non-Infernal Powers in which the Infernal realm has taken a personal interest. Whenever she uses one of these Powers in a way that is not sinful, it has an unpleasant side effect. This is always harmful, and often recognizably Infernal, and the severity varies depending upon the Power’s application, so that extremely good works cause even more terrible evil. The effect is not obviously linked to the use of the Power, and in fact it may seem completely unrelated. It always manifests at about the same time as the use of the Power, however, though the character may not be aware of this.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Some potential side effects might include:</p></div><div class=\"el-ul\"><ul class=\"has-list-bullet\"><li data-line=\"0\" dir=\"auto\">Illness and disease among local people or animals.</li><li data-line=\"1\" dir=\"auto\">Open sores and other painful wounds.</li><li data-line=\"2\" dir=\"auto\">Distrust and a bad reputation among strangers.</li><li data-line=\"3\" dir=\"auto\">Infernal auras in the surrounding area.</li><li data-line=\"4\" dir=\"auto\">Negative or sinful Personality Traits.</li><li data-line=\"5\" dir=\"auto\">Additional botch dice on a particular type of roll.</li><li data-line=\"6\" dir=\"auto\">Demons suddenly causing havoc in the region.</li></ul></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The forces that wreak vengeance cannot cross Magic Resistance or effects like <em>Aegis of the Hearth</em> that keep demons away, yet they can still sense when these Powers are put to good use, and they retaliate however they can.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character may not know about these circumstances, but once she realizes the relationship between her Power and these side effects, they usually seem much worse, as paranoia and guilt may cause her to worry about the potential harm her Powers may cause. Hell hopes that this makes using the Power for good seem too great a sacrifice.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Vengeful Powers may be taken as a Hermetic Flaw, as applicable to Hermetic magic. In that case, the effect triggers whenever the character performs magic that is without sin. It is more commonly associated with Supernatural Abilities, however.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"vengeful-powers","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926913982,"modifiedTime":1730929087739,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Ytoo8KfrGvikhYsb","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Supernatural Nuisance","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Supernatural entities of a certain kind interfere in your life in minor ways whenever you are around them. This differs from Plagued by Supernatural Entity in that the nuisances do not have any long-term plans. This could represent a ghost that haunts you, or general enmity from faeries towards you.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"supernatural-nuisance","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922915946,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"YuC3hLQzyC1wZtCX","sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Wrathful (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are prone to anger over the smallest issues, and your rage when you are thwarted in something major is terrible to behold.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"wrathful-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730929014883,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"Z6hqtYkYzIxEhyEa","sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Leprosy","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character has leprosy. A leper has a permanent –2 modifier to her Living Condition (with an additional –1 if she lives in a leper colony), and whenever she undergoes an Aging Crisis (page @@) the leper sustains a Heavy Wound in addition to any other result. Lepers cannot gain a positive Reputation due to a pungent rotting smell that they emit.&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"leprosy","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730464885884,"modifiedTime":1730929087752,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZPMUjdcKbca0qfhc","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Deteriorating Power","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Like the Variable Powers Virtue, this Flaw reduces the effectiveness of one of the character’s powers (Greater, Lesser, or Ritual) over time. This penalty is linked to either the character’s (age / 10), (Might Score – Might Pool / 5), or Warping Score. For example, a magic character with Deteriorating Powers linked to age and an age of 25 would have one of his powers reduced by 3 magnitudes.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"deteriorating-power","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730012463983,"modifiedTime":1730929087766,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZhF5TTvEEPRktv8C","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Diabolic Past","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You were associated with diabolists, and though you have escaped their evil ways, you are still haunted by your upbringing and the memory of acts best left unspoken. Perhaps your parents were diabolists, although you were not, or maybe you joined a cult but soon repented and fled. Your former associates still take an interest in your activities and whereabouts. Unfortunately. You may purchase the Ability Infernal Lore, even if you are normally not permitted to buy Arcane Abilities.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"diabolic-past","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756701291,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"ZiRJy95F3QpN9yA7","sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Social Handicap","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You have some trait that keeps you from interacting easily with other people. This impairs your dealings with most of society, causing penalties of –3 on appropriate rolls. Examples include morose temperament, unworldliness, an unpleasant odor, or tactlessness.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"social-handicap","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922625910,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"ZopPdiXNPq8Y0n2K","sort":4300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Outsider","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You belong to a group that is both readily identifiable and distrusted or disliked. Examples in most of Europe include Jews, North Africans, and Arabs. For sagas set in Egypt, this Flaw is appropriate for Europeans.</p><p>If you live in society, take the Major version. You are shunned and often persecuted because of this, and your life and freedom may occasionally be in peril. You have a bad Reputation of level 1 to 3 (depending upon how easy it is to identify you) among members of the dominant social group of your area.</p><p>If you spend most of your life in a closed group, such as a city ghetto or covenant, where people like you are accepted, take the Minor version, as you are only shunned if you leave your home, and have somewhere relatively safe to run to if you find trouble. You still have the bad Reputation among members of the dominant social group, but do not meet them so often.</p><p>As a general rule, companions should take the Major version of this Social Status, as they probably interact with wider society often enough for it to be a major problem. Grogs may take the Minor version.</p><p>If the saga takes the character to an area where they are a member of the dominant culture (an Egyptian who lives in a covenant in Ireland travels to Egypt, for example), the troupe should decide on a suitable Social Status for the character. This should normally be a Free Social Status Virtue, unless there are established facts in the character’s background that suggest a different choice.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"outsider","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"49M5jwoqSphEsyDt","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730529260850,"modifiedTime":1730929087779,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZqPpnypQdLYo4EuT","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Faerie Friend","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have an ally among the fay. How much assistance you can get depends on the power of the friend — a small faerie with (relatively) minor powers can accompany you on a day to day basis. Powerful faeries have other business, and may only be available to answer questions and provide guidance, not to accompany you around on your adventures. Your ally is fully sentient, has its own powers, and can speak when it chooses. You may want to have another player act the part. While a faerie companion can be a great boon, it can also be a terrible burden. If it is nasty or mischievous, it could cause trouble for you everywhere. Characters with this Flaw can purchase the Arcane Knowledge Faerie Lore, even if they are normally restricted from purchasing it.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"faerie-friend","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730785525316,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","_id":"ZvbIAJWd4ro8lFTH","sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Reclusive","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You do not like being disturbed or interrupted. You feel that an intrusion by another upon your time is unnecessary at best, and an insult at worst. You are very reluctant to be dragged into public places, or group activities, and generally complain when you must participate. Note that this is often a bad Flaw for a player character, unless there is a good reason why that character needs to stay out of play most of the time (for example, he is played by the alpha storyguide).</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"reclusive","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"ZzhdTHRV2S5M8PHQ","sort":3500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Bound to (Realm)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">The character is no longer able to survive in the mundane world, and sickens if it is outside a particular sort of supernatural aura for an extended period of time. The character must live in a supernatural aura of 5 or greater to remain healthy; if it spends most of a season outside such an aura, make a Stamina Roll against an Ease Factor of (9 – Size). If you fail the roll, the character sustains a Heavy wound, unless the previous season it also failed such a roll, in which case it sustains an Incapacitating wound instead. Choose the realm (Divine, Faerie, Infernal, or Magic) to which the character is bound when you take the Flaw.</span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"bound-to-realm","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918474210,"modifiedTime":1730929087792,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"aAaTw2CsCHageQxu","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Ability Block","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are completely unable to learn a certain class of Abilities, for some reason. This may be Martial Abilities, or a more limited set of the others. A profound inability to master logic would rule out Artes Liberales, Philosophiae, any Law, Medicine, and Theology. Alternatively, you might be unable to learn any languages other than your native tongue. It must be possible for your character to learn the abilities in question in the absence of this Flaw, but she need have no intention of doing so. You may only take this Flaw once.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"ability-block","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"aL5XgJBR5jxV5ZUy","sort":4400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Church Upbringing","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This Flaw covers children schooled by the Church and mostly raised by clerics as well, a fate befalling some orphans, bastards, Gifted children, and other misfits. The Church may act out of charity or a wealthy individual may have paid to discreetly get a difficult child out of the way. This secluded upbringing leaves the character less knowledgeable about the rest of society, which he finds unstructured, uncouth, and confusing. The player must spend 25 experience points from the normal budget on Artes Liberales, Latin, Music, Organization Lore: Church, or Theology. Unless the character has a Virtue that permits it, no other experience points may be spent on Academic Abilities.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"church-upbringing","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729919180579,"modifiedTime":1730929087805,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"aMtcO6bba3iOvRj3","sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Unlucky","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character is exceptionally unlucky, and is frequently dealt a bad hand by the forces of chance. He gets a –1 to –3 penalty (at storyguide’s discretion) on rolls in situations based on luck rather than skill or talent, depending on how much luck is involved. It would be wise for him not to take part in games of chance.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"unlucky","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926574511,"modifiedTime":1730929087817,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"aRyWFn3ZrFESEuY4","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Horrifying Appearance – Snake Legs","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You have no legs, and instead your hips give rise to two or more snake-like tails; you should consider how you survived childhood with this horrific deformity. Your movement is not hindered under most circumstances. You can hide this deformity under clothing, but you cannot move without revealing it, leaving you feigning being crippled as well.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"horrifying-appearance-snake-legs","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730455639273,"modifiedTime":1730929087831,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"aaehglsgGKbTFOWp","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Inconstant Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character’s magic is easily distracted, and it stutters and starts. Spells that require his guidance (e.g. concentration, or aimed spells) after being cast are not immediately responsive, as if the character must focus the spell’s attention, and spells that are triggered by a condition (such as <em>Waiting Spells </em>or enchanted devices) take about two minutes to activate, as if the magic had wandered off when the caster was not watching it carefully. Any magic items he creates with constant effects are interrupted at sunrise and sunset; the magic is not seamless. The character suffers a –3 penalty to all Finesse rolls.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"inconstant-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730457851487,"modifiedTime":1730929087846,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ag4JUiXEj4BJwbPf","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Outsider - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_da50amwz3qe","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You belong to a group that is both readily identifiable and distrusted or disliked. Examples in most of Europe include Jews, North Africans, and Arabs. For sagas set in Egypt, this Flaw is appropriate for Europeans.</p><p>If you live in society, take the Major version. You are shunned and often persecuted because of this, and your life and freedom may occasionally be in peril. You have a bad Reputation of level 1 to 3 (depending upon how easy it is to identify you) among members of the dominant social group of your area.</p><p>If you spend most of your life in a closed group, such as a city ghetto or covenant, where people like you are accepted, take the Minor version, as you are only shunned if you leave your home, and have somewhere relatively safe to run to if you find trouble. You still have the bad Reputation among members of the dominant social group, but do not meet them so often.</p><p>As a general rule, companions should take the Major version of this Social Status, as they probably interact with wider society often enough for it to be a major problem. Grogs may take the Minor version.</p><p>If the saga takes the character to an area where they are a member of the dominant culture (an Egyptian who lives in a covenant in Ireland travels to Egypt, for example), the troupe should decide on a suitable Social Status for the character. This should normally be a Free Social Status Virtue, unless there are established facts in the character’s background that suggest a different choice.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"outsider-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925287269,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"VkWchgUydFoqpyYF","_id":"akEuoaa40yZyV0PT","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Close Family Ties","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Your family is one of the most important things in your life, and still supports and aids you whenever possible, even at personal risk. Family members do not hesitate to do you any favor that is within their power, and can call on their friends and neighbors to help you. It works both ways, however; your family will require help from you some day.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"close-family-ties","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730785474169,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","_id":"auUHRF64J1UTEk36","sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Uncertain Faith","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Whether through a flaw in the character’s understanding of doctrine, a moral turmoil, the disheartening absolution of repeated sins, or exposure to conflicting philosophies, he finds it hard to fully express devotion to his faith. Some element of doubt stands between him and the Divine, and all rolls for holy influence, tempering an aura, invoking God’s aid, or invoking a saint or <em>baraka</em> (see <em>Realms of Power: The Divine Revised Edition,</em> pages 38–41, 87, and 103) suffer a –3 penalty.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character also has an “Uncertain Faith” Personality Trait at +1 that describes this conflict or doubt, which always provides demons with an opportunity to sow further doubt through their Obsession power (<em>Realms of Power: The Infernal</em>, page 31).</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Supernatural Abilities originating from the Divine, including Methods and Powers, are not penalized. This Flaw is not compatible with the True Faith Virtue.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"uncertain-faith","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926380401,"modifiedTime":1730929087860,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"b3ULJ7TOUsj82388","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Study Requirement","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are unable to study magic from books or vis alone. You must study in the presence of the appropriate Art. For example, you need to sit next to a brook or pond to study Aquam, or a large fire to study Ignem. Growing things are good for Creo, decaying ones good for Perdo. As your knowledge grows, you need to work with larger and larger quantities. See the Study Bonus Virtue on page @@ for a list of examples.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You may take both Study Bonus and Study Requirement.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"study-requirement","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922883028,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"bTx0fucDGVAXxqMp","sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Incompatible Arts","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>For some reason you are completely unable to use two combinations of Techniques and Forms. For example, you may be unable to use Intellego Herbam and Intellego Animal. You may not use these Arts together even if one or both are requisites. This Flaw may be taken repeatedly with different combinations, but may not be combined with a Deficiency (see page @@).</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"incompatible-arts","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756701442,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"cK3iD5aLVDuP2YNR","sort":2600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Gullible","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>There is one born every minute — and it is this character! He is an easy victim of ruses, stories and teasing lies. People lying to him get a bonus to their Guile rolls of +1 to +3. </p><p>Depending on how bright or sharp-witted he is, he might not fall for obvious lies, denials of things that are evident or common knowledge. However, he most likely falls for lies that are even remotely plausible, and if he has no idea whether or not something is true, he is almost certain to believe it. This could, for instance, be whether or not there are mischievous faeries under the bridge. If you really want the character to not fall for something, make an Intelligence + Folk Ken Stress roll against an Ease Factor equal to the Communication + Guile roll of the person telling the tall tale. Recommended modifiers to the Ease Factor are +0 for obvious lies (ones that someone without the Flaw would certainly not believe), +6 for outlandish tales and +9 for things which could be true, or lies told by someone in authority, or who has expert knowledge of the subject at hand.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"gullible","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730015296369,"modifiedTime":1730929087873,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"cPl1BkBsODNNroIp","sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Magical (Being) Companion","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character is accompanied by an intelligent magical being, one that is smart enough to follow orders or disobey them on its own initiative, which the character must regularly look after. This might be an animal, a spirit, a human-like creature, or even an animate object. <em>Realms of Power: Magic</em> contains extensive rules for designing such characters, but they can also be made following the guidelines and examples in Chapter 13 of this book. A grog-level character might be essentially an extension of the character’s will, while a companion-level character might follow instructions but often do what it thinks is best, and a magus-level character might be condescending or wild, and rarely act except on its own initiative.&nbsp;</p><p>A particularly common example is a magical animal that’s smart enough to follow your orders or to disobey them on its own initiative. The smaller and more innocuous the creature, the more intelligent it is. A ferret or crow is as intelligent as a human, a wolf is very cunning, and an animal the size of a horse is simply more intelligent than normal. The creature has a Magic Might score of 10 – Size.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"magical-animal-companion","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758110122,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","_id":"cRzwQYZ64UMR3xFa","sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Unbearable to (Beings)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This Flaw is associated with one of three classes of beings: mundane humans, demons, or divine beings. These last two include characters associated with the Divine or the Infernal realms, respectively, through Supernatural Virtues or Flaws, as well as beings with Divine or Infernal Might.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">These beings are extremely disturbed, frightened, and possibly enraged by the character’s presence. She suffers an additional –3 penalty on all social interactions with them, which adds to the –3 penalty normally associated with The Gift. Only characters with The Gift or Magical Air may take this Flaw, and it cannot be combined with the Blatant Gift.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You may not take this Flaw more than once; characters who are Unbearable to more than one kind of being should take the Blatant Gift instead.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"unbearable-to-beings","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926336841,"modifiedTime":1730929087886,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ceLokDlDqhwa8fqc","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Greedy (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You like to eat and drink, and do so to excess whenever given the chance. You are probably fat, but may not be if you rarely have the chance to indulge.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"greedy-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"cwlWFjTQqvjYRt7n","sort":3600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Beloved Rival -Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>For a Minor Story Flaw, the character has a rival who is both fiercely protective of him and obsessed with opposing him at every turn. For Tytalan magi, this rival is usually an older maga, most likely the magus’s former teacher, or possibly an elder apprentice of the character’s master. Much like the Enemies Flaw, the rival periodically causes trouble for the magus; however, she jealously guards the privilege of making the magus’s life a misery, and often steps in to remove obstacles that are not of her own making. The rival genuinely believes that her opposition benefits her victim, and desires to see him prosper through adversity.</p><p>If the character takes on the role of the beloved rival for another character, then this is a Major Flaw. The character generates stories by causing trouble for their rival, and also has to react when someone else tries to harm them.</p><p>Such relationships are a tradition of House Tytalus, and may be mutual. When the rivalry is mutual, the troupe may allow the character to take both the Minor and Major versions of this Flaw. This will mean that the rivalry will be a very important feature of the whole saga, and thus the whole troupe must consider whether they want that.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"beloved-rival-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918038141,"modifiedTime":1730929087901,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"d53UgVXCBya5kKQg","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Envied Beauty","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character’s beauty draws revulsion and jealousy. This envy does not strike everyone, but vain persons of the character’s gender are particularly susceptible to it. Characters with this Flaw may avoid its penalties by refusing to reveal their beauty to the world, which creates its own complications.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">A character lacking a positive Presence score may not have this Flaw.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"envied-beauty","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013086557,"modifiedTime":1730929087914,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"dCNCjVyDkQM6apba","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"The Falling Evil","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character occasionally suffers convulsions and blackouts. Convulsions occur randomly and infrequently; for any given event, the storyguide should secretly roll a stress die, and if the result is 9 or more then a convulsion will occur at some point during that event, as chosen by the storyguide. This spasm causes random movements and hallucinations, leaving the character temporarily Incapacitated. She collapses to the ground and twitches, and you can make a Stamina roll against an Ease Factor of 9 every round; success means that the convulsion ends, although the character is reduced to the Dazed Fatigue level following a fit. The Falling Evil is usually caused by possession by demons (<em>Art & Academe</em>, page 48), but that form of the illness is usually temporary in nature. The character does not seem to have a disease, and cannot naturally recover from this affliction. It may be that it stems from a different source. In Ancient Greece and Rome, it was called the “divine illness,” as it was believed that the gods spoke to those who had such fits.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"the-falling-evil","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730925953107,"modifiedTime":1730929087928,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"dEZy0Yp2tBOYmssd","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Creative Block","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[{"origin":"Compendium.world.de-ars-flaws.Item.dHpl3fZP8yC0vdeV","duration":{"rounds":null,"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.labActivities.inventSpell","value":"-3","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["labActivity"],"subtype":["inventSpell"],"option":[null],"hidden":false}},"name":"Creative block","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","_id":"TOWcvT3wafSvNx4X","type":"base","system":{},"description":"","transfer":true,"statuses":[],"sort":0,"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":1729923801911,"modifiedTime":1729923841486,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"}}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have problems creating new things in the lab. You take a –3 penalty to all Lab Totals unless you are using a Laboratory Text or being taught. If you experiment, roll twice as many dice on the experimentation table.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"creative-block","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758467930,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"dHpl3fZP8yC0vdeV","sort":2700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Stockade Parma Magica","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Because of your restricted understanding of Parma Magica, you cannot suppress your Parma once it is erected. Any friendly spell or magical affect must penetrate your Parma Magica to affect you, just as if it were a hostile spell.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"stockade-parma-magica","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922790235,"modifiedTime":1730929087942,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"dRnKX1FCeGgZHEGF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Oath Of Fealty","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You have sworn an oath of loyalty and support to someone outside the covenant, and sometimes they call on you to uphold your vow. Magi are forbidden from taking Oaths of Fealty by the Hermetic Code. Some don’t let that stop them.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"oath-of-fealty","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730918778810,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"dUy7fTisv4LR9Esn","sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Lecherous (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You seek sexual contact with as many people as possible. Note that you need not be any good at seduction; skill here merely changes the kinds of problems you encounter.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"lecherous-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756701551,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"dVn9A3EjbwXYXaSP","sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Hunchback","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have a deformed body that gives you a grotesque appearance and hinders your movements. You are at –3 to all rolls involving agility and balance. Communication rolls that involve good looks are at –3.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"hunchback","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"dXRm9r4Nz8UjUaYm","sort":4500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Oversensitive - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Something that others find merely unpleasant you consider intolerable. Examples might include an oversensitivity to disrespect, to slovenliness, or to impiety. If you are the violent type, you may start fights with those who offend you.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"oversensitive-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"e0aTpsurRFXMDlCl","sort":3700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Meddler (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You want to fix other peoples’ lives: arrange matches, teach children to sew “properly,” or tend the sick. You waste a lot of time and energy on such endeavors, and people usually resent it.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"meddler-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"eUPeue5xeSjLhX9Y","sort":3800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weird Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your control over magic is somewhat loose, perhaps due to Twilight effects or idiosyncratic training. Roll one extra botch die when you roll a zero on stressed spell casting rolls, apart from your other botch dice. Botches from this die should be strange or bizarre rather than dangerous, and if the Weird Magic botch occurs along with a regular botch, the results could be truly spectacular.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"weird-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928884795,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"eVrohXNLj3aRAx5F","sort":2800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Seeker","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are a self-proclaimed member of the Seekers, a loose organization of competitive magi searching for ancient magic and arcane artifacts. Much of your life is spent in pursuit of these items. Your interests may occasionally clash with other interests of your House or covenant. More details about the Seekers can be found on page 15 of <em>Houses of Hermes: True Lineages.</em></p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"higher-purpose","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922090788,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"eYaYxWrVhyiIkQ5j","sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Unruly Air","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character has a penchant for stirring up situations, making pleasant events better and unpleasant ones worse. Whenever the character is in a social situation with multiple people, his slightest behavior will subtly push others to extreme behavior. He is either the life of the party, or its death, depending on the prevailing mood of the crowd. His influence is linked to his magical nature, so that others with Magic Resistance are not influenced by him.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"unruly-air","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926715588,"modifiedTime":1730929087955,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ekJu4LBDFmQw7i6A","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Depraved - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character seeks to undermine religion whenever possible, and generally tries to avoid the Dominion. He might sin in public, teach misinformation about the tenets of the faith, or show obvious disdain for holy things. He is not necessarily an infernalist; it could be that he simply despises organized religion, dislikes the Divine realm, or does not believe in God. He might even be persuaded to attend services, though he does not take any of it seriously and is likely to disrupt the ceremony with his discomfort and ignorance.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"depraved-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730012402421,"modifiedTime":1730929087968,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"f5j1l7p3xczXMgdj","sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Proud (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You believe that you are more important than just about everybody, and expect the appropriate respect. Magi may admit one or two equals, but do not believe that they have any superiors. Mundanes will admit social superiors, but still believe themselves to be fundamentally better than, say, the king.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"proud-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"f7VeJwJUObrNRp6s","sort":3900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Pessimistic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You always expect the worst. You may try to enjoy yourself, but you are sure that anything that can go wrong, will, and will pick on you.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"pessimistic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"f8k9PO44L50Kleht","sort":4000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Oversensitive - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Something that others find merely unpleasant you consider intolerable. Examples might include an oversensitivity to disrespect, to slovenliness, or to impiety. If you are the violent type, you may start fights with those who offend you.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"oversensitive-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730529389151,"modifiedTime":1730756701635,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"fJEO7C5bS2oMb0kT","sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Failed Journeyman","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character has been expelled from a guild due to past illegal or questionable practices. He may not practice his trade in town nor sell his goods there. The character is expected to find another means of livelihood, although no other guild will accept him, so many such men must find a way to practice their trade illegally. He has a bad Reputation of 2 in town.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"failed-journeyman","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"socialWestern","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"49M5jwoqSphEsyDt","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013567768,"modifiedTime":1730929087981,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"fObWKkAJyrXNF29z","sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Excommunicate","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>For your crimes against God and the Church, you have been cast out of your faith, undoing your baptism and driving you from your religious community. You have a bad reputation at level 3 within the Church, and cannot benefit from the sacraments.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"excommunicate","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013409489,"modifiedTime":1730929087996,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"fWsTbnShDaXp0GE7","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Crippled","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You either have no legs, or your legs are completely useless. You may have lost them in an accident or as a punishment. You cannot walk, although you may drag yourself along the ground, or push a trolley around with a stick.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"crippled","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756815434,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","_id":"g6j4TunVd5Wa9nmh","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Failed Master","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Either through faulty management or illegal business practices, the character has run his workshop into the ground. He must work as a journeyman if he wants to practice his trade legally in town. The character has a bad Reputation of 4 in town, and it will be difficult for him to regain his legal status as a master.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"failed-master","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"socialWestern","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"49M5jwoqSphEsyDt","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013622481,"modifiedTime":1730929088009,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"gJ18fmKhP5XX8NIb","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weak Personality","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This character doesn’t feel strongly for or against anything and lacks the unique traits most people have to make them really stand out. Consequently, all Personality Traits must be between +1 and –1. When making personality rolls, treat any roll above 6 as merely 6. The character may have no other Personality Flaws or Virtues or Flaws that grant Personality Traits. Depending on the personality of the observer, he may seem a complete pushover with no opinion of his own, insensitive because he rarely shows strong emotion, or simply lacking in initiative to those seeking leadership and guidance. These elements result in a –1 or worse (at the storyguide’s discretion) modifier in most social situations for obviously being a cold fish. Finally, he will never be known for his great loyalty or pious nature, and will have a hard time winning respect or getting promoted. His lack of enthusiasm for the Church in particular might be viewed as a lack of faith. On the plus side, he might occasionally be seen in a positive light since he never disagrees strongly.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"higher-purpose","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730928738048,"modifiedTime":1730928738048,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"gP9I6f0pYBAsHz6H","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Primogeniture Lineage","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character is in line for Primus of House Verditius. Either her parens, or her parens’s parens, is the Primus, and she is one of his descendants. She is at least three places removed from the Primus. She receives undue attention from the House, as they eye her as a prospective Primus. The other magi in the same line may also regard her poorly, hoping to somehow remove her from her heritage. Her ascension to Primus is far from guaranteed, and many events may transpire to prevent her from claiming the title. This should foster very political stories for her. This Flaw can only be taken by magi of House Verditius, as a maga who has left the House is no longer a candidate for Primus. In her case, it would be no more than an interesting feature of her background.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"primogeniture-lineage","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730919528571,"modifiedTime":1730929088022,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"gRtIYRHUyO7MhPoB","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Blackmail","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have information that some powerful person would prefer kept hidden. You receive payments or services in return for your silence, and you may occasionally demand special favors. Don’t push your luck — your victim may decide it isn’t worth the cost, or silence you permanently. This benefit has a yearly value of about 50 silver pennies, possibly more if you keep the pressure on. You should detail and record the specifics of this arrangement.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"blackmail","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925519700,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","_id":"gUc5vU2E9uj4iR34","sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Restricted Learning","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character is incapable of learning new things without assistance. Pick five Abilities at character creation; you can only apply experience points to these Abilities. The character cannot learn any new Abilities on her own; she must receive experience points from Teaching or Training to develop a new Ability or to improve one that is not part of the initial five. Furthermore, she cannot use an Ability with no score, even if it can normally be used untrained. Any Supernatural Abilities from Virtues she possesses are added to the list of Abilities to which she can apply experience points. All mundane animals are required to take this Flaw. A character with Intelligence rather than Cunning is not a mundane animal for these purposes.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"restricted-learning","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730921767234,"modifiedTime":1730929088035,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"gYNaPYrhwERBoxhL","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Animal Companion","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are accompanied by a loyal, intelligent (but mundane) animal that can obey simple commands. Your relationship with it is very close. If it should die, you would be profoundly upset.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"animal-companion","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758110122,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","_id":"gqX0jcd6KRJr9Wuj","sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Rebellious - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You react adversely to any attempt to impose authority over you, and work against those who are in command. You do not necessarily have any desire to be a leader yourself, but you don’t like to be pushed around.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"higher-purpose","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730921349106,"modifiedTime":1730921349106,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"gx4byvcLxJXaviDl","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Cursed Guile","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This is the Flaw for “the boy who cried wolf,” and probably results from Infernal influence. The character has three extra botch dice when using Guile. More importantly, the character is rarely believed, even when he is being honest. He must make a Communication + Guile roll against an Ease Factor of 9 in order to be believed when he tells the truth at important moments. For example, if the character is returning from a scouting mission, and you fail his Guile roll when he reports back, the maga may assume that he has been deficient in his duties; perhaps she thinks that he never went scouting at all, but instead went to the nearest town to entertain himself. This character may prefer the company of animals to that of people, as they do not respond to subterfuge.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"cursed-guile","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729925970678,"modifiedTime":1730929088049,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"hI3suSMmK8mCMvub","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Gabai","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Appointed by the community council, the gabai is the local tax collector. It is his responsibility to ensure that Jewish taxes, payable to the community on such things as wine and meat, are collected from all adult males.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The gabai has a –2 negative Reputation of “Tax Collector” in his community. This Flaw is compatible with any other Free Social Status Virtue.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"gabai","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"socialJewish","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"49M5jwoqSphEsyDt","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014925243,"modifiedTime":1730929088062,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"hQml8CZejNfLjV5j","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Busybody","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You usually know everything that is going on among your friends and acquaintances, especially in private matters. You are always interested in rumors and gossip, and are frequently able to extract personal secrets from people. Among magi the language is more dignified, but the idea is the same: you keep tabs on the Hermetic community (your covenant, your House, and nearby covenants — at the least). However, magi probably don’t have much knowledge of what’s going on among the lower-class members of their covenant unless they choose to apply this Flaw specifically to such people at character creation.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"busybody","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"hUd2p6H3uD03EmU3","sort":4100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Poor Living Conditions","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Either because of this character’s own poor living conditions, or those of people he is in frequent contact with, he is more susceptible to the rigors of daily life. The character has an additional –1 Living Conditions Modifier. This is cumulative with the character’s base Living Conditions Modifier.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"poor-living-conditions","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730919330435,"modifiedTime":1730929088075,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"hfcgZRZzzT21oYQB","sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Companion Animal","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character is the Animal Companion of another character (either a player character or a storyguide character) and therefore has little control over his own life. He is largely dependent on his master for food and shelter, and has an additional Personality Trait of “Loyal to Master” which represents this bond. Among people who know his master, the character is treated better than he would be, perhaps as that person’s pet or bodyguard. Others most likely treat him as a brute or a dumb beast.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"companion-animal","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"49M5jwoqSphEsyDt","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729919491434,"modifiedTime":1730929088090,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"hmLPbWzdpPAlNcjS","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Obsessed - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are fixated on some prized object, action, or ideal. This interferes with your accomplishment of more immediate tasks. Examples might include obsessive protection of magi to the point that you attack those who insult them, or obsessive neatness where you keep yourself spotless and deride those who do not.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"obsessed-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730528840217,"modifiedTime":1730929088103,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"hxOV9KRdqCq30WD1","sort":1450000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Master of None","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Either by choice or circumstance, this character never seems to be able to stick at a task or job for longer than a season, usually following the work as it moves through the year. As a result, this character can’t apply any experience points earned through an Advancement Total to an Ability or Art that they have already applied experience points to this year. Where they can’t be applied to a different Ability or Art, the experience points are lost.&nbsp;</p><p>Experience points gained through other means, such as Secondary Insight, are unaffected and may be applied normally.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"master-of-none","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730465525350,"modifiedTime":1730929088116,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"hzrji4HrfIxtSaPy","sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Mute","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You cannot speak; perhaps your tongue was cut out. You probably use rudimentary hand gestures and grunts to communicate your needs. You can still understand languages perfectly well, and may learn to read and write if you have an appropriate Virtue. Note that magi with this Flaw get a –10 penalty to all spellcasting, although this may be offset by taking the Quiet Magic Virtue (page @@). A magus with this Flaw can be assumed to be able to make sounds, which are sufficient to allow normal use of the Voice Range.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"mute","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756701797,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","_id":"iENdtqeg3rJmbZwZ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Simple-minded","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You can only think about one thing at a time — guarding the bridge, hunting for a missing ring, or hiding in the trees for example. You become easily confused unless others give you very clear instructions. When unexpected circumstances pop up, you find them difficult to deal with.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"simple-minded","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"iP5d4y0IAvkk69iL","sort":4200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Clumsy Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have trouble targeting your spells accurately. Any aiming roll is subject to disastrous failure: an aiming roll of 0 is automatically a botch. (Aiming rolls do not count as mystical rolls for the purposes of gaining Warping Points.) You receive a –3 penalty to any rolls involving Finesse.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"clumsy-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758343798,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"ipd5HOY5fhswuDkI","sort":2900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Lingering Injury","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character suffers from an old injury that won’t heal properly, resulting in a –1 penalty to all rolls involving physical activity. If he botches a physical action, he aggravates the injury and the penalty becomes –3 (recovery from aggravation is as for a Light Wound). This condition worsens with age, so multiply whatever the penalty is by 1 + (Decrepitude Score)</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"lingering-injury","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730465001009,"modifiedTime":1730929088130,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"j6k9MDAPZvGPZKKQ","sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Rigid Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You cannot use vis when you cast spells. Thus, you cannot increase your spell rolls or cast Ritual magic. You can use vis in the laboratory, or to refresh a Longevity Ritual.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"rigid-magic","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921879698,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"jIsvr2TtwuVWeYt8","sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Imagined Folk Tradition Vulnerability","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Although this flaw closely resembles a Delusion, Imagined Folk Tradition Vulnerability has other game mechanical effects as well. This character utterly and sincerely believes that he has been touched by the fay, and that they have granted him his special skills — whether or not any such exist. So, naturally, he is convinced that he is as vulnerable to traditional wards and folk magic as the fey. Whenever there is talk about such folk remedies, or people around him try to perform them, he does his best to dissuade them. If he can get away with it, he removes or sabotage such wards; for instance, he sneaks around at night and removes any warding marks or materials at doorways. Finally, he exhibits strange behavior around active wards or ritualistic actions. This could be refusing to shake hands with a person right after they have drawn the sign of the cross, or flinching whenever salt is flung over someone’s shoulder. On the plus side, this Flaw allows the character to purchase a score of 1 (but no more) in Faerie Lore at character creation. This is because he needs a rudimentary knowledge of the fay and the wards against them in order to be able to act this way. Without such knowledge, his behavior is based on what he <em>thinks </em>such wards might be.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"imagined-folk-tradition-vulnerability","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730457690670,"modifiedTime":1730929088144,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"jdZsFgG78ud9idG7","sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Short-ranged Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Halve your Casting Totals whenever you are not touching the target of the spell. Halve your Lab Total when designing an effect or spell that has a range greater than Touch, including Eye.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"short-ranged-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922310744,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"kFdWnjS4lnxYIcWU","sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Monastic Vows","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have taken vows of poverty, chastity, and obedience to a religious superior. This covers the vows taken by mendicant friars, as well as those taken by monks and nuns strictly speaking.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"monastic-vows","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756701863,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"kQF1a7UbB0lCnMno","sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Higher Purpose - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Let others concern themselves with petty matters, you have a nobler goal. This purpose should be altruistic, like freeing an oppressed people or bringing peace between the Order of Hermes and society.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"higher-purpose","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925326313,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"kYEKF1GiCGw5ZD6z","sort":4300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Cyclic Magic (negative)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>As with the Hermetic Virtue, your magic is attuned to some cycle of nature and is less potent at specific times. You have a –3 penalty to all Lab Totals and Casting Scores during that time. The penalty applies to Lab Totals even if the negative period does not cover the whole of the season. The length of time during which you are at a disadvantage must be equal to the time when there is no penalty.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"cyclic-magic-negative","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758486957,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"kYinPompF1UaPAUz","sort":3000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Nocturnal","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your natural body rhythms try to keep you sleeping until noon. You are at –1 on all rolls made between dawn and midday. Conversely, you have little difficulty staying up at night. Though you enjoy no special benefits in the dark, your companions may decide to saddle you with night guard duty on a regular basis to use your attributes to best effect.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"nocturnal","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730871953117,"modifiedTime":1730929088157,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"kgoHo1PQgiZDz2jw","sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Cabal Legacy","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7hmf0zx1tdl","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"},"core":{}},"system":{"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">This Flaw applies to magi beginning play as Initiates in a Mystery Cult; it is not required of those seeking Initiation later, by story actions, nor is it required for membership in one of the four Mystery Houses. It allows a magus character to be designed with cult Virtues as normal Virtues, part of the standard ten Virtues and Flaws &mdash; something not otherwise possible. These Virtues and Flaws are accounted for exactly as normal: in particular, Flaws acquired now do not later count as past Ordeals. Note that if a particular Virtue requires some other specific Virtue or Flaw, then this is still required during Cabal Legacy character generation.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">The magus&rsquo;s master was an initiate of a Mystery cabal and taught him its secrets. As an apprentice, he was marked by the Mystery. Even if he renounces all the occult trappings of the society, most magi associate him with the Mystery, especially the mystae themselves. When a magus with Cabal Legacy speaks, magi often think he speaks for his entire cabal. When he acts, the mystae often assume he&rsquo;s acting as their agent.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">From time to time (rarely more than once every few years) he is approached by a senior mystae and commanded to perform a laborious task or undertake a bizarre quest on behalf of the cabal, usually requiring a season&rsquo;s worth of activity. Performing this task well increases his status with the mystae and deepens his perceived connections to them. Refusing or bungling the task earns their wrath.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">This Flaw is similar to a Minor version of the Major Story Flaw Favors.</p>","source":"TMRE","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"cabal-legacy","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925543838,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","_id":"kpgFU3o9KP9AJNcU","sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Short of Breath","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character cannot last as long as others when exerting himself and quickly tires during extended physical activity. He receives a –3 penalty to all Stamina rolls to avoid fatigue, including rolls to maintain Concentration.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"short-of-breath","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922249020,"modifiedTime":1730929088170,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"kvFYpBgPtvpJqJ13","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Careless Sorcerer","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are slapdash in your use of magical power, and must roll two more botch dice than normal when casting spells. Note that if you would normally roll no botch dice, you still roll none.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"careless-sorcerer","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758392827,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"kwHsWxXPZ4lsAqXt","sort":3100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Beloved Rival - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>For a Minor Story Flaw, the character has a rival who is both fiercely protective of him and obsessed with opposing him at every turn. For Tytalan magi, this rival is usually an older maga, most likely the magus’s former teacher, or possibly an elder apprentice of the character’s master. Much like the Enemies Flaw, the rival periodically causes trouble for the magus; however, she jealously guards the privilege of making the magus’s life a misery, and often steps in to remove obstacles that are not of her own making. The rival genuinely believes that her opposition benefits her victim, and desires to see him prosper through adversity.</p><p>If the character takes on the role of the beloved rival for another character, then this is a Major Flaw. The character generates stories by causing trouble for their rival, and also has to react when someone else tries to harm them.</p><p>Such relationships are a tradition of House Tytalus, and may be mutual. When the rivalry is mutual, the troupe may allow the character to take both the Minor and Major versions of this Flaw. This will mean that the rivalry will be a very important feature of the whole saga, and thus the whole troupe must consider whether they want that.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"beloved-rival-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918032699,"modifiedTime":1730929088185,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"l6S9gyvqQkCmLV7c","sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Corrupted Abilities","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">One or more of the character’s Abilities was taught to her by a demon, or came through some other corrupted source of study. Use of a corrupted Ability for a selfish or sinful action receives a +3 bonus to the roll. Succeeding in a roll because of this bonus (that is, when without it the roll would have failed) means that the character immediately acquires 5 experience points in that Ability. However, uses of the Ability that are neutral or selfless receive a –3 penalty, and if you fail the roll because of this penalty, the character loses 5 experience points in the Ability.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Any use of a corrupted Ability is an unholy act, which can be sensed by Divine Powers. You may only take this Flaw once, though you can choose to have it affect multiple Abilities if you wish.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"corrupted-abilities","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729923541009,"modifiedTime":1730929088198,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"lAYj3sPaU0U6UHvm","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Dwarf","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[{"_id":"7Ku4M7y6PCGfxK66","changes":[{"key":"system.vitals.siz.value","value":"-2","mode":2,"priority":null},{"key":"system.characteristics.str.value","value":"-1","mode":2,"priority":null},{"key":"system.characteristics.sta.value","value":"-1","mode":2,"priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"origin":"Compendium.arm5e.flaws.voE3EGIFczw3bxPe","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["vitals","characteristics","characteristics"],"subtype":["size","str","sta"],"option":[null,null,null]}},"name":"Dwarf","description":"","statuses":[],"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null},"img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","type":"base","system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are the size of a child. Your comfortable walking speed is two-thirds that of a normal person. Your Size is –2, so the severity of wounds you take increases in three point increments rather than five point increments (see page @@). You take a –1 penalty to each of Strength and Stamina, which may reduce each Characteristic as low as –6. You cannot take this Flaw and Giant Blood (page @@), Large (page @@), or Small Frame (page @@).</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"dwarf","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756835940,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","_id":"lM884WIUYka1rCFp","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Exiled Atlantean","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character is an exiled Atlantean; she is tainted by her contact with the surface world, and cannot return to her magic regio. This exile is enforced by the very nature of the magic regio to which the Atlanteans are native, so there is no authority figure to which she may appeal, or any obvious method of returning to favor. The exile applies even if the Atlantean left her native magic regio involuntarily. More details about the Atlanteans can be found in <em>Realms of Power: Magic,</em> page 90.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"exiled-atlantean","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013456978,"modifiedTime":1730929088211,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"lRTtaDbr3ToTGIk0","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Anchored to the (Land)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">The character suffers from feelings of loneliness and depression when she cannot see or hear a particular type of environment. In game terms, the character has a –3 penalty to all rolls when traveling through any other sort of environment (it is assumed that once the character has time to recover from the journey, she will find some reminder of her natural environment to help her rest). For example, a character who is Anchored to the Sea would suffer the penalty when traveling overland, but once settled can easily comfort herself — with the sound of the sea heard in a seashell, perhaps.</span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"anchored-to-the-land","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729917740058,"modifiedTime":1730929088224,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"lXfd16ncWZAE6XLS","sort":2700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"University Dean","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character is the head of a university, having already acquired his doctor in (faculty) license. The character has been chosen to lead the university, overseeing external affairs with the town and internal affairs between students and masters. Though prestigious, the position imposes serious demands on the character’s time. The character can expect many interruptions in his teaching during the school year. The character must have the Virtue Doctor in (Faculty), be at least 40 years old, and can not have the Poor Flaw or any other Flaw that grants a Bad Reputation.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"university-dean","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926549814,"modifiedTime":1730929088238,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"laPxg9UIrEaz8hze","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Infamous Master","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Your master was a diabolist, bumbler, fool, widely despised, or held in contempt for some other reason. Most magi expect little better from you. Even if you’ve done nothing wrong, you are treated as though you don’t deserve to be a member of the Order. You have a bad Reputation of the appropriate type at level 3 among magi.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"infamous-master","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756701979,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"lmsGCE8dCJ3g8vdE","sort":3200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Corrupted Spells","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character has learned at least 30 levels of formulaic spells from a source that has been corrupted in some way. Use of a corrupted spell for a selfish or sinful action receives a +3 bonus to the character’s Casting Total and Penetration Total. Succeeding in a roll because of this bonus (that is, when without it the spell would have failed or cost Fatigue) means he immediately acquires 5 experience points towards mastery of that spell. However, uses of the spell that are neutral or selfless receive a –3 penalty, and if you fail the roll or he fatigues himself because of this penalty, he immediately loses 5 experience points. If this would result in negative experience, he forgets the spell completely.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Any use of a corrupted spell is tainted and appears unholy. You may only take this Flaw once, though it can affect as many of the character’s spells as you wish.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"corrupted-spells","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729923695199,"modifiedTime":1730929088251,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"lzDPZiWEeNnvcJvU","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Unstructured Caster","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You have never quite mastered the intricacies of spellcasting, and are unable to perform Formulaic magic without extreme effort. You cast all Formulaic spells as though they were Ritual spells (including the need for vis), and you may not learn Ritual spells at all. You cast Spontaneous spells normally.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"unstructured-caster","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730926767521,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"mBOuAXPR4VxTdHws","sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Regular","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character lives according to a strict religious rule, which leaves little time for other activities. The character must spend one of his free seasons on the seasonal activity of worship. This is particularly suitable for monk and canon characters, but it is not compulsory. The Regular Flaw is compatible with Wealthy and Poor, but a Poor Regular character effectively has no free seasons and may be unsuitable as a player character. Magi can be Regular.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"regular","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730921659633,"modifiedTime":1730929088265,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"mSuV1C7TvDmSCyL2","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Poor Formulaic Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are simply not very good at formulaic magic. Subtract 5 from every roll that you make to cast formulaic spells. This does not apply to Ritual spells.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"poor-formulaic-magic","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730919282331,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"mkKh9J0j1hKtnkj5","sort":3300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Hedge Wizard","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Because of your esoteric magic, other magi distrust you, and more importantly, grant you no respect. You start with a negative Reputation within the Order of Hermes at level 3 as a hedge wizard, even though you are a member of the Order.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"hedge-wizard","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730455382745,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"mu2GafgaQSJBZVC0","sort":3400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Broken Vessel","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character is constantly aware that her supernatural powers may only be temporary. Failures using those abilities represent the ebbing away of the power that sustains them. When a zero is rolled on any Stress Roll (not Simple Roll) for any of her Supernatural Abilities, Powers, or in casting spells, she loses 5 experience points from that Ability or an Art involved in the Power or Spell. If the roll then botches, the character automatically loses enough experience points to reduce her score in the affected Art or Ability by one full level (or 5 experience points, whichever is greater). </p><p>Characters may only take this Flaw if they have at least one Supernatural Ability or Art normally improved through experience points.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"broken-vessel","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918674430,"modifiedTime":1730929088279,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"nERX8p6jLj0VzQ1R","sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Small Frame","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[{"_id":"E6e4bvPR5eVb7IJq","changes":[{"key":"system.vitals.siz.value","value":"-1","mode":2,"priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"origin":"Compendium.arm5e.flaws.dkNtErVVH7UdqraZ","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["vitals"],"subtype":["size"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Small Frame","description":"","statuses":[],"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null},"img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","type":"base","system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are of a lighter-than-average build. Your Size is reduced to –1. This means that the severity of wounds you take increases in four point increments, rather than five point. (See page @@). You cannot take this Flaw and Giant Blood (page @@), Large (page @@), or Dwarf (page @@).</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"small-frame","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922593708,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"nFbX2jgTUTuxw9cc","sort":4600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Ambitious - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You want to be the most successful or powerful person in the world in some respect. You will not be distracted into doing things that do not contribute to your ambition, and are very eager to do things that advance it.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"ambitious-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"nQkwHuhnpGA68Wid","sort":4400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Enemies","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Someone is causing trouble for you, such as a local baron or bishop, a band of outlaws, or a really nasty innkeeper. The enemy must be powerful enough to endanger you — this is best agreed on with the storyguide and the rest of the troupe.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"enemies","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730785290374,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"nVk0h09fmOcZVfok","sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Greedy (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You like to eat and drink, and do so to excess whenever given the chance. You are probably fat, but may not be if you rarely have the chance to indulge.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"greedy-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730784575004,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"nZiBrxgFK6QudEMn","sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Proud (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You believe that you are more important than just about everybody, and expect the appropriate respect. Magi may admit one or two equals, but do not believe that they have any superiors. Mundanes will admit social superiors, but still believe themselves to be fundamentally better than, say, the king.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"proud-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730919590637,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"nfEvxDy0ulx83HGE","sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Feral Upbringing","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">You grew up in the wilderness, either raised by wild animals or surviving on your own. For much of your life you could not speak, and knew nothing of human ways. Now that you have joined human society (or the covenant), you have learned to understand some basic spoken phrases, but civilized life is still a mystery you want little part of. You may only choose beginning Abilities that you could have learned in the wilds. In particular, you may not start with a score in a Language. In your first five years you gain 120 experience points, which must be split between (Area) Lore, Animal Handling, Athletics, Awareness, Brawl, Hunt, Stealth, Survival, and Swim.</span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"feral-upbringing","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925525963,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"nsDRhg5BBqa73tPl","sort":4700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Poor Student","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[{"_id":"5409wAuYd96NvKfx","changes":[{"key":"system.bonuses.activities.teaching","value":"-3","mode":2,"priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"origin":"Compendium.arm5e.flaws.t0CYrytE5z6bDwSS","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["activities"],"subtype":["teaching"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Poor student","description":"","statuses":[],"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null},"img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","type":"base","system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are bad at learning new things. Subtract 3 from all Advancement Totals derived from teaching and books (that is, you have no penalty to adventure experience, exposure, practice, studying from vis, or training), but do not reduce a total below one. If you could learn something without this Flaw, you still learn a bit.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"poor-student","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"nvsPu2BTxzCXXFIT","sort":4800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Avaricious - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You want money, lots of money. When you have it, you do not spend it, but hoard it so that you can count it. You can be avaricious about physical things other than money, such as books or raw vis. In this case, you do not use the things you hoard, nor do you allow others to use them.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"avaricious-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730757150911,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"nyiQ8TgTM2uxwluN","sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Delusion","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You believe wholeheartedly in something that just isn’t so. Examples include that you are a magus (if you are not), that you are the Pope’s child, or that your imaginary friend is real.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"delusion","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"oATSUqY7nckgcBdc","sort":4500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Grudge","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>For some reason, based on a past event, the character holds a strong grudge against someone who is part of his normal social circles, and with whom he would be expected to have cordial relations. He is constantly interested in what the other person is doing, what they are working on, and how he can outdo them.&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"grudge","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730015250892,"modifiedTime":1730929088291,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"oPhVy7dhfgfgv2EP","sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Monastic Vows (Hermetic)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You have taken vows of poverty, chastity, and obedience to a religious superior, which means that you cannot own vis and must only possess functional magic devices. You cannot marry, and many magi might interpret that as prohibiting binding a familiar. You must do what your master commands in service of your order, though in return you can expect aid and assistance when needed.&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"monastic-vows-hermetic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730465976773,"modifiedTime":1730929088305,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"oUQtMJD5yh5UUKUV","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Missing Ear","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You cannot accurately locate the direction of sounds, and suffer a penalty of +3 to hearing rolls.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"missing-ear","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"or7MkBLvN0wQ0Cmw","sort":4900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Enfeebled","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You cannot exert yourself for longer than a few seconds. Any need for rapid movement, such as combat or a chase, leaves you helpless. Long hikes are likewise beyond your capability. You are unable to learn Martial Abilities or any other skills involving physical exertion, since you cannot train in them. If you are a magus, you lose double the normal number of Fatigue levels from casting spells, but you may carry out Laboratory activities as normal.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"enfeebled","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756851915,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","_id":"ovsfPBolAljI0ZOg","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Servant of the (Land)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Some powerful magical creature has saved the character from death or granted a similar boon, and in return the character has been set a task. Possible tasks include: preaching a message, operating a lighthouse, or preventing hunting in a certain area. Usually the task is either difficult or time-consuming, and while it remains incomplete the character has the Minor Personality Flaw: Prohibition, but this does not count toward the character’s total number of Virtues and Flaws. The Prohibition means that if the character does not spend at least one complete season every year working toward his assigned task, a curse afflicts him. Possible curses include: a magical compulsion to return to the land where the character must explain himself to his master, turning into an animal, or acquiring a Supernatural Flaw.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"servant-of-the-land","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922139157,"modifiedTime":1730929088318,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"p2GZ62Vd6AxS3KVL","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Slow Reflexes","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character does not react well to surprises. He receives a –3 to his Initiative total in situations warranting a quick response.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"slow-reflexes","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922546177,"modifiedTime":1730929088331,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"p5QdiBy1Ueo7FAYF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Fickle Nature","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The character swings between two types of personality behaviors that are directly opposite. There is no middle ground, so the character is always either displaying traits of one behavior or the other. Select a Personality Trait at +4, and its opposite at +4. Typical Personality Traits are: Happy and Sad, Energetic and Lazy, Confident and Diffident, or Proud and Humble.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"compulsion-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014136985,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"p8dTuoBO16IEZsea","sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Wanderlust","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character feels compelled to travel with a passion that is so strong that he cannot spend more than a season in the same place. The character can only spend two (nonconsecutive) seasons each year in the same area, and must spend the intervening seasons traveling to different locales — places he has never been. If for some reason he cannot travel, he will become very uncomfortable; this discomfort should cause stories in the same way as the travel would.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"wanderlust","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730927240688,"modifiedTime":1730929088345,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"pGBYpEfDBhib0DZe","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Magical Air","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>People and animals react to you as if you had The Gift. You may not take this Flaw if you actually do have The Gift; see The Blatant Gift (page @@) instead.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"magical-air","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756702192,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","_id":"pGWog6CECZTQGnoB","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"The Constant Expression","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The maga forms the center of a magical maelstrom, perpetually casting non-fatiguing Spontaneous magic effects. The resulting effects are minor due to the nature of non-fatiguing Spontaneous magic but are likely to cause distraction and/or other problems. Though non-fatiguing, the effort of marshaling the magic into less dangerous forms is tiring and the maga is considered to have lost one long-term Fatigue level which cannot be regained through sleep. </p><p>The effects produced by the constant expression may target anything that the maga could normally target with spontaneous spell, including herself, although they are more likely to target things touched by or seen by the maga. </p><p>The maga may actively concentrate in order to suppress this automatic magic entirely, making an initial Stamina + Concentration simple roll against Ease Factor 3 + (Warping Score). On a failure, a further roll is allowed every two minutes after the maga has composed herself. If the magic has been suppressed, the maga may cast Spontaneous and Formulaic spells normally. </p><p>In order to cast Ceremonial or Ritual magic the maga must make a Concentration roll as described above. One attempt can be made every 15 minutes, a successful attempt sufficient to cover the duration of the casting. Nevertheless, the maga suffers a number of additional botch dice equal to her Warping Score. </p><p>The constant expression of magic also makes laboratory work inherently risky. Any laboratory the maga works in is treated as having a free Flaw providing a Safety penalty of –3 (see <em>Covenants</em>, page 111). </p><p>Penalties from foreign auras, or from effects such as Aegis of the Hearth, may dampen the constant expression. Where the penalty reduces the casting total to 0, no magic is expressed. </p><p>The player should decide, based on personality, sigil, and favored arts, how the constant expression most often manifests, though the storyguide may vary the actual effect scene-by-scene.</p><p>Conciatta of Bonisagus, a brilliant theorist of the tenth century who extended Hermetic magic to affect the Divine, Faerie, and Infernal realms, famously suffered from this Flaw, which is otherwise extremely rare. Other magi may assume that a character who has it has some connection with her. More details of Conciatta can be found in <em>Legends of Hermes.</em></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"the-constant-expression","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729923392419,"modifiedTime":1730929088358,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"plpaJcQ5ZQwsbay3","sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Fragile Constitution","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You are sickly and weak. You suffer a –3 penalty on all rolls to recover from wounds and diseases.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"fragile-constitution","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[{"origin":"Item.7IEjzpaoy6ImHpC5","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.traits.recovery","value":"-3","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["vitals"],"subtype":["recovery"],"option":[null]}},"_id":"5tGhOmmMppGsv3tZ","transfer":true,"name":"-3 to wound recovery rolls","description":"","statuses":[],"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null},"img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","type":"base","system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo"}},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730921663138,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"ps6J77kiz2sV0OqT","sort":5000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Blind","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have little or no sight. Using missile weapons is futile, reading is impossible, and navigation in unknown territory is difficult to say the least. Blind magi can detect targets by other senses, and thus are less limited than people trying to use missile weapons. However, blind magi cannot aim spells without magical aid.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"blind","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756807343,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","_id":"q7FmeqhlLesjPF2V","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Vow","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You have sworn to do something difficult, and breaking your vow is a serious matter. Example vows include never raising a weapon, never speaking, or living in poverty. If you do fail to uphold your vow, you must perform some kind of atonement, whether it be religious penance or coming to terms with your failure in some other way. A Vow that is a Major Flaw must be a vow to do something, rather than refrain from something, so that it can drive you to act.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"vow","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730927090160,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"q9UbuneZ74Q3zCNC","sort":4600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Dhimmi","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">You are a non-Muslim living under Muslim rule. If you are adult and male, you must pay the <em>jizya</em> head tax, and all <em>dhimmis</em> must abide by certain social restrictions (described in the sourcebooks for these areas of Mythic Europe — see <em>Realms of Power: The Divine, The Cradle and the Crescent, Between Sand and Sea,</em> and <em>Lands of the Nile</em>), in return for which they receive tolerance and protection from the Muslim authorities. The actual amount a <em>dhimmi</em> has to pay in <em>jizya</em> varies, but rarely exceeds a <em>dinar</em> (a gold coin) per year.</span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"dhimmi","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730012550729,"modifiedTime":1730929088372,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"qN60vPB59cOVHSKO","sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Blatant Gift","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>People immediately realize that there is something strange about you, even if they do not know you are a magus. Animals are extremely disturbed, frightened, and possibly enraged by your presence. You suffer a –6 penalty on all interaction rolls with normal people and animals, and should see page @@ for further discussion of this Flaw’s effects.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"blatant-gift","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730757351674,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"qTVw6H0wZEI8hrhL","sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Castratus","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">You were castrated before puberty, leaving you beardless and somewhat effeminate compared to most men. Social rolls involving characters from Latin culture suffer a –3 penalty. Under Byzantine law you may not marry, although you may adopt children. In Byzantine culture, this may have been an astute career move on your guardians’ part, as eunuchs can attain positions of power. Elsewhere, it was probably the result of an accident or an assault. This Flaw is only available to characters who were born with testicles.</span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"castratus","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729919029682,"modifiedTime":1730929088389,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"qyf6nUzMHNlmCM4w","sort":2300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Compassionate - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You help anyone who is wounded or in trouble. You cannot bear to see suffering in others, although you happily drive yourself to exhaustion.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"compassionate-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"r2iLYRm8sM9wzifT","sort":4700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Necessary (Realm) Aura for (Ability)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Due to some connection with a given supernatural realm, the absence of a given supernatural aura has a pronounced effect upon the character’s ability to focus on certain tasks. The character has a –3 penalty to any totals he generates with a particular Ability when not in the right aura. A character may take this Flaw once for any particular Ability. The chosen Ability should be one which the character is likely to use frequently, such as in service to the covenant or to support his day-to-day activities.&nbsp;</p><p>When applied to Craft or Profession Abilities, this Flaw also reduces the character’s capability to support himself by reducing the number of Labor Points (as described in <em>City &amp; Guild)</em> he accumulates each season when not working within the appropriate aura.</p><p>Troupes should think carefully about how a character would be limited by taking Magic (which covers most covenants) or Dominion (which covers most other human settlements) aura. If the character would not be limited, the Flaw should not be allowed.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"necessary-realm-aura-for-ability","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730528352976,"modifiedTime":1730929088403,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"rASfPILy2rtStvaf","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Folk Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">The character is capable of performing very minor acts of magic through his knowledge of scraps of occult lore. Choose one (Realm) Lore that is the key Ability for this magic; he may learn this Ability at Character Creation even if he is normally unable to take Arcane Abilities. The choice of (Realm) Lore also determines which supernatural realm his magic is aligned to for the purposes of aura modifiers. He can only create spells in one narrow area, which must be one of the following four options:</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\"><strong>Abjuration:</strong> Creates a ward against animals or supernatural creatures. Uses the Rego Animal or Rego Vim guidelines.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\"><strong>Divination:</strong> Acquire magical senses that detect health, wealth, and mental state. Uses Intellego Corpus, Intellego Mentem, and Intellego Terram guidelines.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\"><strong>Healing:</strong> Grants a Recovery bonus for either wounds or diseases, and aids the birthing of children and livestock. Uses the Creo Corpus or Creo Animal guidelines. Infernal Lore cannot be used to produce this type of effect.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\"><strong>Evil Eye:</strong> Causes minor acts of mischief like pain, blight of crops, hair loss, sneezing, and so forth. Uses the Perdo Corpus, Perdo Animal, or Perdo Herbam guidelines. Divine Lore cannot be used to produce this type of effect.</span></p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">To cast a spell the character must expend a Fatigue level, whether the spell succeeds or fails. He must also spend at least 15 minutes preparing the spell, during which time he needs unbroken concentration and access to his “magical” materials (while necessary, these materials offer no benefit to the casting). The spell is designed exactly like a Hermetic spell. The Casting Total is equal to (Stamina + (Realm) Lore + Aura modifier + stress die) / 2. Penetration is calculated in the normal fashion: Casting Total – Spell Level + Penetration modifiers. You may pick this Virtue more than once, to acquire expertise in a different category of spells. Each time you choose this Virtue, you can align it to the same Realm as before or pick a different one, although a character cannot have access to both the Divine and Infernal Realms.</span></p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"folk-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":true,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014697060,"modifiedTime":1730929088417,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"rAVeXzaIexc43wcT","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"True Love (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You have found the one person meant for you in all of creation, and the bond between the two of you cannot be sundered. Whenever you are suffering, in danger, or dejected, the thought of your love will give you strength to persevere. In dire need, he may even come to rescue you. More often, he will be in trouble and need rescuing. If any enchantment keeps you from your true love's side, the power of your devotion can probably break it. Your love is higher than mortal magic, and no magic can make you hate your love, or make you truly betray him. Your True Love must be a non-player character. To have another player character as your True Love, see the True Love Virtue on page @@.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This Story Hook may be renamed 'True Friend' to cover characters with whom you are very closely linked, but not in a romantic way.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">If the True Love is significantly weaker than the player character, and not able to provide useful assistance in most cases, this is a Major Flaw. If the True Love is competent, equal to or better than the player character, then this is only a Minor Flaw. The True Love may need rescuing occasionally, but more often she will involve the player character in her plans.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"true-love-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730926109879,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"rNr5RkUuoi09SHRy","sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Age Quickly","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xc1hyhkw51","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Probably due to a curse or a magical disaster, you age twice as fast as normal people. Your effective age (which applies as if it were your actual age when creating a Longevity Ritual, and when making rolls on the aging table) increases two years for every year that passes, and you make two aging rolls each year. It is possible to halt or slow the decline by supernatural means, such as Longevity Rituals, but they must deal with your effective age, not your chronological age.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"age-quickly","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925612643,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","_id":"rXbP7wHbhjR0KCcG","sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Mentor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A person of some importance, wealth, or wisdom has taken an interest in your life, and at times provides you with minor material aid and advice. However, at some point your mentor will have a small favor or two to ask of you. He might not necessarily like your relationship with the covenant — perhaps you must keep it a secret. The Mentor must be an NPC.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"mentor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730758110122,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"w0VVgqRCx0opq0TL","_id":"rl8nqpqJYlXLw4qX","sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Humble","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are humble, always willing to believe that others are more skilled and better than you. You do not necessarily underestimate your own abilities, you just think others are better.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"humble","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"rp19sdt1rF8IPBmr","sort":4800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Susceptibility to Warping","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your character’s constant exposure to magic has made him more susceptible to supernatural Warping than he might otherwise be.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">In any year in which the character gains a Warping Point from any Realm or any source (including Longevity Rituals, living within an aura, and powerful supernatural effects), the character gains one additional Warping Point associated with that same Realm. This means that if he gains a single Warping Point from each Realm in a year, he gains four additional Warping Points, one from each Realm, at the end of that year.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">These additional points do not contribute to Wizard’s Twilight or to other events caused by the acquisition of Warping Points as they accrete slowly over the course of the year.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"susceptibility-to-warping","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730925754374,"modifiedTime":1730929088431,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ruSCSJud0pB2pgjQ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Optimistic (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are convinced that everything will turn out for the best. This is not overconfidence, as you accept that you might well fail. Even if you do, however, you are sure that circumstances will mean that everything works to your benefit.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"optimistic-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925618516,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"s4tpWNUDzr9V1wCE","sort":4900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weak Magic Resistance","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Any form of Magic Resistance you generate is much weaker under relatively common circumstances which are fairly easy for an opponent to utilize, such as when you are wet or facing away from the caster of the spell. If the conditions are met, do not subtract the level of the effect from the casting total before calculating Penetration. You would be well advised to keep your weakness from being discovered by too many potential enemies.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"weak-magic-resistance","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928634863,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"sANYY0BD9j5oyMJh","sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Failed Student","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character has studied for a specific university license and failed his final examination. If he passed earlier exams, he may have a scholastic Social Status Virtue showing how far he got. (Obviously, this cannot be Doctor in (Faculty).) The character has a Bad Academic Reputation of 2.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"failed-student","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730013713722,"modifiedTime":1730929088444,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"sFNKdeRdCq39Hjun","sort":5200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Raised in the Gutter","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This character was raised on the margins of society. She is able to use her social abilities normally with those of the lower and middle classes, but doesn’t know how to act among her “betters.” When using Charm or Guile, it is obvious that she’s from the bad part of town, and this makes convincing people to do what she wants harder (–3 on rolls). She can use Etiquette normally if she’s holding her social place (which means staying silent and doing exactly what she’s told) but suffers a –3 penalty if she tries to go beyond this.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"raised-in-the-gutter","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730919677516,"modifiedTime":1730929088458,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"slg0GP1TIf5hVsEB","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Compulsion - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have an unfortunate urge that you have trouble resisting. Examples include drinking, sex, perfection, bragging, or gambling.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"compulsion-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729919746582,"modifiedTime":1730784455858,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"sqV1xQJDvQ8Ghd3h","sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Envious (Major)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You believe that everyone has it better than you do, and that they don’t deserve their good fortune, while you do. Thus, you try to ruin their lives and take their goods for yourself. (This is not a good Flaw for a player character, as it is likely to lead to conflict with the other players.)</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"envious-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730784519618,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"t3ofx6TilAHmLAoM","sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Tormenting Master","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your master does not believe you have successfully passed the apprentice's gauntlet (the test of becoming a magus). He periodically troubles you with political moves and indirect attacks. This Flaw is only applicable to magi, although other characters could take an analogous Story Flaw.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"tormenting-master","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730926020036,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"tII28gR2qre1V87U","sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Stuck in Your Ways","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Having come from a covenant, this character knows how things must be done to best serve the needs of covenfolk and magi alike. Only, his new home does things differently. And they’re wrong. When making Stress Rolls against his Profession Abilities or any Ability concerning his new covenant, such as Leadership or Folk Ken, this character uses the lower of that Ability score and his current Covenant Lore Ability for his current covenant. Note that bonuses from Puissant or other Virtues still apply to the roll.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This Flaw can also be applied to organizations other than covenants, such as abbeys, universities, guilds, or churches.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"stuck-in-your-ways","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922835180,"modifiedTime":1730929088473,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"tR2cyXAo3IRzxat2","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Savantism","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The character’s family was cursed by faeries; his mother tripped over a hare while pregnant with him; or he was born on horseback. He is physically capable, but simple-minded and slow-witted. He has half the standard experience points at character generation, all future Advancement Totals are halved, and he may not begin with an Ability above 3. However, with one favored Ability, he is exceptionally gifted. This Ability can improve normally, is limited to a score of 6 as a starting character, and has +3 to all rolls related to its specialization rather than just +1. The Ability must be something he could reasonably have access to learn; there would need to be an extraordinary background story for a savant who is a master of the longsword!</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Most savants will be like the tragic fool whose precocious skill with horses has gone forever unnoticed, but some may have more esoteric talents. If the favored Ability requires a Virtue, such as Academic or Martial Abilities, then he must have that Virtue as normal; a mathematical savant would need a Virtue such as Educated to learn Artes Liberales. Magi may well desire the company of certain specialists: a Jerbiton maga would appreciate an artistic savant, for example. Similarly, a Failed Apprentice may have been left stricken with savantism when his Gift abandoned him, but he retained remarkable clarity on the Code of Hermes, becoming a valued clerk to a Quaesitor.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"savantism","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730922002581,"modifiedTime":1730929088486,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"tU1VVWexuzU7pOlW","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Fettered Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>All of your spells and the effects of any magic items you activate are Arcane Connections to you. You cannot take this with the Virtue Tethered Magic, as the Virtue already includes this effect.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"fettered-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014059947,"modifiedTime":1730929088499,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"tk6lELqAByIGVaZI","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Bigamist","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character has two entirely separate lives, in two cities, and moves between the two on some pretext, most likely trade. Bigamists have two spouses, and maintain two households, which they must pay for. If you are using the rules in <em>City and Guild,</em> the merchant’s annual cost of maintaining his business rises by (6 x Wealth Multiplier) Labor Points. Some bigamists mitigate this expense by pretending to be of lower status in their alternate life, which reduces the additional Labor Point cost by half (to 3 x Wealth Multiplier).</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"bigamist","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918073809,"modifiedTime":1730929088512,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"u28gGLChk9t4B8nj","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Hallucinations","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character is afflicted by vivid hallucinations which seem to be true visions, but rather than coming from a higher power, they are figments of her imagination and fantasy. She finds these visions particularly troublesome, and seeks meaning in them where there is none to be had. Coincidence might mean that some part of her hallucinations comes to pass, which only furthers her belief that there is meaning within them. If the character also has the Visions Flaw, then some of her visions are true, but most of them are meaningless jumbles of nonsense generated from within her mind.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"hallucinations","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730455274581,"modifiedTime":1730929088526,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"uCwJCPZeNlOt6YRm","sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Compassionate - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You help anyone who is wounded or in trouble. You cannot bear to see suffering in others, although you happily drive yourself to exhaustion.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"compassionate-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730784446441,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"uJ4mBeNmcmSXoVIe","sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Depressed","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have a dark outlook on life, seeing little point in acting and taking no pleasure in anything that happens.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"depressed","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"uQc2d6g7wZvRMJzk","sort":5000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Careless with (Ability)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">The character is particularly reckless when it comes to a particular Ability, chosen when this Virtue is taken. This Ability should be one that is important to the character, or the troupe may veto the choice of this Flaw. When she fails, she does so dramatically. Whenever she rolls a zero when using the Ability, that zero is treated as a botch. She may need to roll extra botch dice depending on the circumstances, but she always suffer the effects of at least a single botch. This Flaw may be taken more than once; each time, it applies to a different Ability.</span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"careless-with-ability","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729918971670,"modifiedTime":1730929088540,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"uXWVlSgzVJGER7Za","sort":2500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Palsied Hands","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your hands shake uncontrollably, which makes casting spells or holding objects difficult. All rolls involving holding or wielding an object are made at –2, including weapon skills. Magi and others who rely on hand gestures to work magic must roll an extra botch die when casting a spell.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"palsied-hands","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925628335,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","_id":"uXg6Wfna8RXN7vJn","sort":5100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weak Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Your magic is particularly bad at penetrating Magic Resistance. You halve the normal Penetration Total for all spells, and only get half the normal benefit when instilling Penetration into an item. Note that you halve the Penetration Total, after subtracting the spell level and making any adjustments for the use of Arcane Connections. You do not halve the Casting Total and calculate Penetration from that.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"weak-magic","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928666466,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"ufhX9nDba0vWbs6G","sort":3600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Rolling Stone","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">The rolling stone gathers no moss, and neither does this character. She has moved from village to village so often that she finds it difficult to create attachments in the community. All social rolls have a –1 penalty within the community.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"rolling-stone","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730921934264,"modifiedTime":1730929088553,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"uitI90XjH9UY2HPR","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Viaticarus","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">At some point in the character’s past, he was at death’s door, and as a result a priest performed the sacrament of Extreme Unction. The purpose of this sacrament was to remit him of all venial sins, and prepare him for the journey beyond (the viaticum); but against all expectations, he survived. This leaves him in a spiritual no-man’s land, not one of the dead, but neither wholly of the living. Because of this, he is immune to the temptations of demons, and therefore cannot be affected by their Obsession power; he simply does not register to them as a soul in need of corruption. However, his skin has an unusual pallor, and his eyes are sunken. People may smell a charnel odor about him. These effects are subtle at first, but as he ages, he gradually comes to resemble a corpse more and more, resulting in a penalty to all social interaction rolls equal to his Decrepitude score.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">He has difficulty crossing thresholds where unquiet spirits are not welcome; if a person with a (Realm) Lore of 1 or more has set up a traditional ward, such as a line of salt or an iron nail laid on the lintel, then he cannot enter the protected building or area. Further, although he does not have a Might score, he is repulsed by any magical warding that can keep out a creature with a Might score aligned to Corpus or Mentem (including the <em>Aegis of the Hearth</em>), regardless of its level or Penetration. However, both types of exclusion can be negated if he is invited to cross by the person who established the ward, or someone who lives within. He can still touch individuals with Magic Resistance, since he has no active power around him.</p></div><div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">If the character’s status is known in the community in which he lives, he should take the Outcast Social Status Flaw.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"viaticarus","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730927005498,"modifiedTime":1730929088567,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"uoijXOn6es4Cy6ks","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Plagued By Supernatural Entity","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ciwmacrmzmm","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Story","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Some supernatural being interferes in your life on a fairly regular basis. It may even have your best interests at heart, but the result is that you get dragged into stories. Suitable examples would be a demon trying to corrupt you, an angel trying to save you, a faerie playing games with you, or a ghost continuing the agenda she had while alive.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"plagued-by-supernatural-entity","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925638618,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","_id":"v6BG20RLD2zYz6hT","sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Hatred (Minor)","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You hate someone or some group so much that hurting them dominates your life. The target of your hatred must not be someone you could easily overcome.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"hatred-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"vJxHyBxKD8G7xi93","sort":5100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Craving for Travel","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"internal-embed markdown-embed is-loaded\">The character suffers from feelings of loneliness, boredom, and depression if he does not expose himself to new experiences. He can stave off the boredom for a while, but if he remains in one place for more than a season, he suffers a –1 penalty to all rolls and totals until he experiences a change in scene. This penalty rises to –3 after a year of boredom. This character is probably the first to volunteer for a mission beyond the covenant gates, and may even spend part of each year in a different location such as the nearby wood. This Flaw might seem to make the character unsuitable for life at a covenant, so you should decide what it is at the covenant that means he keeps coming back. Perhaps it is the love of his life, the camaraderie, or perhaps just the feeling that he fits in here.</span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"craving-for-travel","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729923773058,"modifiedTime":1730929088581,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"vQKeWt28PFxOBjaX","sort":2400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"No Hands","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[{"_id":"An5Lfzt4Pt7JfN8c","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"origin":"Compendium.arm5e.flaws.hbzPg2zlVXLhUPrX","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":[],"subtype":[],"option":[]}},"name":"No hands","description":"","statuses":[],"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null},"img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","type":"base","system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have no hands. Any activity requiring hands is impossible, and magi with this Flaw take a –5 penalty to all Casting Scores. This may be offset by taking the Subtle Magic Virtue (page @@) or the Still Casting Spell Mastery ability.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"no-hands","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756702515,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","_id":"vtNYk7rCruGkXhYa","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Limited Magic Resistance","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are less able to resist magic than other magi. You gain no bonus from one of your Form scores to Magic Resistance, though if you are caught without your Parma Magica, you retain a Magic Resistance of 0. You may take this Flaw multiple times, for multiple Forms.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"limited-magic-resistance","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756702530,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"vwTUKLvdV8V2GPkz","sort":3700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Consumed Casting Tools","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character’s casting tools are magically consumed after he uses them. It takes an hour to make a new casting tool. Regular casting tools do not allow the magus to make multiple copies of them, so he may not stock up on casting tools. Making a casting tool for a spell that already has a casting tool erases the magical connection from the existing tool to the spell. The magus does not need a laboratory to make casting tools. This Flaw may only be taken by Verditius magi.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"consumed-casting-tools","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729923440791,"modifiedTime":1730929088596,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"w1IUgoaCkwNu6ki4","sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Noncombatant","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You have no interest in combat, nor do you have any ability with it. You might be unreasonably afraid of combat, or a complete pacifist, or prone to freezing and doing nothing.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"noncombatant","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"w8ju3avRiQATsKCe","sort":5200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Compulsive Lying - Major","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Telling the truth is really hard for this character. This does not apply in situations where the answer is evident and any lie would be transparent; he does not claim that the sky is green under normal conditions. However, when he cannot be immediately caught out, he finds it hard to avoid embellishing stories, or simply making them up. Perhaps he wants to make himself look good, perhaps he wants to downplay his own part in a conflict, or perhaps he just loves the power of confusing people.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"compulsion-major","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729923277962,"modifiedTime":1730784476383,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"bz0zTiMt6vpLpBEO","_id":"wP9KhHqNrZdEHDgs","sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Unhappily Married","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/story.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You are a Christian who has never been baptized for whatever reason, perhaps because you have some kind of supernatural background that might be undone by the ceremony — many magi believe that baptism impairs The Gift. Your faith is important enough to you that you still strive to be virtuous and attend Mass, though you do not benefit from the sacraments. Most common people who discover this fear and avoid yYoung merchants often marry for financial reasons. The nobility are often required to marry to form or strengthen alliances. The character has married for money or politics, not love, and seeks solace outside his marital bed. Unhappily married characters must hide their affairs of the heart from their spouses, their spouses’ families, and possibly from their partners’ spouses. In many areas, separation due to infidelity is permitted, although this is not divorce. In many such cases the wife’s dowry must be returned, in part or full. In the case of the nobility, this could even lead to a small, local war, or a Feud.ou.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"unhappily-married","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"story","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"HvyHCuxjJNI5yJoA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926451004,"modifiedTime":1730929088612,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"wuDXG2ZNzrMFQBZc","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Difficult Longevity Ritual","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Something in your magical nature makes it difficult to create an effective Longevity Ritual for you. Anyone (including yourself) creating a Longevity Ritual for you must halve their Lab Total. You may create Longevity Rituals for others without penalty.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"difficult-longevity-ritual","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756702577,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"MY0pk5xRqPANrebl","_id":"x6JQEAWPwWaQZu6m","sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Lycanthrope","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xc1hyhkw51","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have been cursed to change form into a dangerous predator (such as a wolf, lynx, or bear) on nights of the full moon (or similar, monthly, astrological events). No items or clothing transform between shapes, and it takes one full round for the full transformation to take effect. You are not immune to normal weapons, and the curse does not infect bite victims. The animal may be detected as a cursed human with an InAn or InCo spell.&nbsp;</p><p>You have the intelligence of an animal while changed, react to all stimuli as an animal, and do not retain any memory of actions taken in animal form, save occasionally in dreams. You may not even realize that you are under this curse. You can still recognize both friends and enemies when changed.</p><p>Lycanthropes may transform into a non-magical animal between Size –1 (wolf) and Size +2 (bear). You have the normal physical characteristics of a shapeshifter (see page @@), except that +3 is added to your Soak score (in animal form only). Furthermore, you are fully healed of all wounds incurred in animal form upon resuming human form (which happens at dawn).&nbsp;</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"lycanthrope","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730756702587,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","_id":"x9UIufdWrsmWfloD","sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"No Sense of Direction","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You are completely unable to follow directions. North, south, east, and west have no meaning to you, and you often confuse right and left. You frequently get lost while traveling unfamiliar paths by yourself, or with others following your lead, and often have to reason your way home or to your destination from first principles. This Flaw is incompatible with the Well-Traveled Virtue.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"no-sense-of-direction","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730871893902,"modifiedTime":1730929088628,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"xTXx2iBWHBGNwbLR","sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Uncontrollable Strength","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">This character doesn’t know his own strength, and at times he has trouble controlling it. This Flaw may not be taken if the character’s Strength is below 0. Whenever he handles delicate or fragile objects, whenever care must be taken to knock somebody out gently, and so on, he risks overdoing it, severely. The character must make a stress roll against an Ease Factor of 6 to avoid using too much power and causing damage of some kind. In addition to this, any Strength Stress Roll uses one extra botch die.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"uncontrollable-strength","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730926415948,"modifiedTime":1730929088642,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"xav1fEz2m52Y0iL7","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Covenant Upbringing","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You were raised in a large, old covenant that has little contact with the outside world. You might have very strange religious beliefs, and you certainly find medieval social and political structures very odd. You may take Latin at character creation, and are likely to have a score in Order of Hermes Lore. While Latin cannot be your native language, you may speak a language closely related to Latin that is spoken only at your home covenant.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"covenant-upbringing","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"xt3PLJQehBqVB7tV","sort":5300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Obsessed - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You are fixated on some prized object, action, or ideal. This interferes with your accomplishment of more immediate tasks. Examples might include obsessive protection of magi to the point that you attack those who insult them, or obsessive neatness where you keep yourself spotless and deride those who do not.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"obsessed-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"xuxJthiC9V4jFOtS","sort":5400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Foreign Upbringing","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>This Flaw is somewhat similar to Covenant Upbringing, but means that the character is a foreigner and comes from a remote or isolated corner of Mythic Europe. He appears and sounds nothing like the locals, has odd customs, habits, and religion (although he need not be pagan), and is quite confused by local society. However, he is not an Outsider, and has been accepted — for the most part. His Native Language is one foreign to the saga, and he needs to learn another language in order to communicate with the rest of the turb. The maximum scores at character creation for locality-dependent Abilities like Language, Area Lore, or Organization Lore, as well as some social Abilities, are half (round up) that which his age normally allows.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"foreign-upbringing","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730014740432,"modifiedTime":1730929088656,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"y1NwSOP3PihpHZmE","sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Gender Nonconforming - Minor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You do not conform to the expected behavior for a person of the gender that your society would assign to you in the absence of social cues such as clothes and behavior. This may mean, for example, that you dress as a member of another gender, or that you structure your life in a way considered appropriate to another gender, or that you are sexually attracted to members of the same gender. It does not necessarily mean that you disagree about what your gender is, although it may. As a Minor Flaw, it does not normally cause you problems, whether because your society accepts your behavior, or because you can turn people who object into newts, or for some other reason. As a Major Flaw, it does cause you problems.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"gender-nonconforming-minor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730015029736,"modifiedTime":1730929088671,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"y6ae9bHE6apPPXkX","sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Deaf","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_g1gywhrffo","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You cannot hear at all. You may be able to speak, but you cannot understand spoken language, which makes communication difficult. Magi with this flaw must roll an extra two botch dice when casting spells with a spoken component, as they cannot hear what they are saying.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"deaf","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925654891,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"JfccfuGi1M1LXZSX","_id":"y9ZryvieNRlVAVpV","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Soft-hearted","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You cannot bear to witness suffering, and causing it brings you sleepless nights. Even the deaths of enemies are painful for you. You avoid danger and try to keep your friends out of it as well. Life and health mean so much that you would rather give up important goals than let another person risk combat. You are easily moved by song and story.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"soft-hearted","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922645536,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"yC5nvM5E92GyZs2V","sort":5500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Devoted Parent/Child","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalFlaw.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The character is extremely attached to a parent or child. Where he goes, she goes also. Separation of more than a day cause s anxiety, and gives a –1 penalty to all rolls due to stress.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"devoted-parentchild","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false,"ownership":null},"effects":[],"folder":"UfPp46NPMX0jIrJv","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730012508362,"modifiedTime":1730929088686,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"yVzK6dskrNOA83IG","sort":2200000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Poor Memory","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You have a very hard time recalling one type of thing, such as names, faces, or places.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"poor-memory","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"ympB9Mjg79teDAWT","sort":5600000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Raised from the Dead","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You died, and were brought back to life through a holy miracle. You begin with at least three Warping points, plus one Warping point for every year that has passed since you were resurrected, and you automatically receive another Warping point every year you continue living. You also have a level 4 reputation in the area where the miracle occurred. You do not remember what happened to you while you were dead, although you may have virtuous impulses that you cannot explain.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"raised-from-the-dead","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"PMTtdepguHpd2YfJ","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730919646468,"modifiedTime":1730929088702,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ytdeMtzKx47UY63b","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Judged Unfairly","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Somehow you come across the wrong way to people, and they universally distrust and underestimate you. You catch no one’s eye, impress no one, and can get no one to take you seriously. If you ever find an exceptional someone who sees you as you want to be seen, you will cling to that person. You cannot gain a positive Reputation in any community, and this Flaw is incompatible with any Virtue that gives you such a Reputation.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"judged-unfairly","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"yz4moTkwMLkJCLHN","sort":5700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Susceptibility to Sunlight","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">Direct, bright sunlight causes you noticeable pain and exhausts you. Attuned to darkness, your eyes are very sensitive, and you suffer from a –2 penalty to all rolls involving sight in bright environments such as a cloudless day. Due to your malediction, you lose one Fatigue level per Diameter if outdoors at noon on a hot summer day, and lose levels more slowly in less-intense light and warmth from the sun.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"susceptibility-to-sunlight","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"FxRILmyYavwmreBA","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730923191062,"modifiedTime":1730929088716,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"z5IqqaDNDLG5HA9A","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Temperate","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<p>You do not over-indulge in any sensual pleasures.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"temperate","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730925834333,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"zT3v4O31fKTqeEgl","sort":5800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Ceremonial Spontaneous Magic","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You need time and effort to focus your Spontaneous magic. You can only cast Spontaneous spells using the rules for Ceremonial Casting (page @@). This Flaw is not compatible with Difficult Spontaneous Magic or Weak Spontaneous Magic.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"ceremonial-spontaneous-magic","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729919073515,"modifiedTime":1730929088731,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"zUozhSFpHugvJhqY","sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Weak Scholar","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zctzc5h7p5","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You don't understand laboratory guidance very well. You get a –6 penalty to Lab Totals when working from the Lab Texts of others, including when re-inventing spells.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"weak-scholar","review_status":"needAE","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730928769735,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"8FTSMAxaThguRoxc","_id":"zhU9EZ1QNUjTK5NB","sort":3800000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"name":"Short Attention Span","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/personality.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_18qw00m8tam","path":"Flaws#/CF_SEP/Personality","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"el-p\"><p dir=\"auto\">You have trouble concentrating. Keeping watch, listening to complex orders, following the plot of a story, or performing other such tasks that require continued attention are usually not within your ability.</p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"type":"personality","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"short-attention-span","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","hidden":false,"tainted":false},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1729832791616,"modifiedTime":1730922497215,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"hXfkbCsUoxlA0bSB","_id":"ziwqxHh53y7xrpgC","sort":5900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
